24Jr 8:18 O my Comforter in sorrow, my heart is faint within me.
24Jr 8:19 Listen to the cry of my people from a land far away£º "Is the LORD not in Zion? Is her King no longer there?" "Why have they provoked me to anger with their images, with their worthless foreign idols?"
24Jr 8:20 "The harvest is past, the summer has ended, and we are not saved."
24Jr 8:21 Since my people are crushed, I am crushed; I mourn, and horror grips me.
24Jr 8:22 Is there no balm in Gilead? Is there no physician there? Why then is there no healing for the wound of my people?
24Jr 9:1 Oh, that my head were a spring of water and my eyes a fountain of tears! I would weep day and night for the slain of my people.
