24Jr 10:16 He who is the Portion of Jacob is not like these, for he is the Maker of all things, including Israel, the tribe of his inheritance--the LORD Almighty is his name.
24Jr 10:17 Gather up your belongings to leave the land, you who live under siege.
24Jr 10:18 For this is what the LORD says£º "At this time I will hurl out those who live in this land; I will bring distress on them so that they may be captured."
24Jr 10:19 Woe to me because of my injury! My wound is incurable! Yet I said to myself, "This is my sickness, and I must endure it."
24Jr 10:20 My tent is destroyed; all its ropes are snapped. My sons are gone from me and are no more; no one is left now to pitch my tent or to set up my shelter.
24Jr 10:21 The shepherds are senseless and do not inquire of the LORD; so they do not prosper and all their flock is scattered.
24Jr 10:22 Listen! The report is coming--a great commotion from the land of the north! It will make the towns of Judah desolate, a haunt of jackals.
24Jr 10:23 I know, O LORD, that a man's life is not his own; it is not for man to direct his steps.
24Jr 10:24 Correct me, LORD, but only with justice--not in your anger, lest you reduce me to nothing.
24Jr 10:25 Pour out your wrath on the nations that do not acknowledge you, on the peoples who do not call on your name. For they have devoured Jacob; they have devoured him completely and destroyed his homeland.
24Jr 11:1 This is the word that came to Jeremiah from the LORD£º
