24Jr 12:14 This is what the LORD says£º "As for all my wicked neighbors who seize the inheritance I gave my people Israel, I will uproot them from their lands and I will uproot the house of Judah from among them.
24Jr 12:15 But after I uproot them, I will again have compassion and will bring each of them back to his own inheritance and his own country.
24Jr 12:16 And if they learn well the ways of my people and swear by my name, saying, 'As surely as the LORD lives'--even as they once taught my people to swear by Baal--then they will be established among my people.
24Jr 12:17 But if any nation does not listen, I will completely uproot and destroy it," declares the LORD.
24Jr 13:1 This is what the LORD said to me£º "Go and buy a linen belt and put it around your waist, but do not let it touch water."
