24Jr 13:24 "I will scatter you like chaff driven by the desert wind.
24Jr 13:25 This is your lot, the portion I have decreed for you," declares the LORD, "because you have forgotten me and trusted in false gods.
24Jr 13:26 I will pull up your skirts over your face that your shame may be seen--
24Jr 13:27 your adulteries and lustful neighings, your shameless prostitution! I have seen your detestable acts on the hills and in the fields. Woe to you, O Jerusalem! How long will you be unclean?"
24Jr 14:1 This is the word of the LORD to Jeremiah concerning the drought£º
