24Jr 46:11 "Go up to Gilead and get balm, O Virgin Daughter of Egypt. But you multiply remedies in vain; there is no healing for you.
24Jr 46:12 The nations will hear of your shame; your cries will fill the earth. One warrior will stumble over another; both will fall down together."
24Jr 46:13 This is the message the LORD spoke to Jeremiah the prophet about the coming of Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon to attack Egypt£º
24Jr 46:14 "Announce this in Egypt, and proclaim it in Migdol; proclaim it also in Memphis and Tahpanhes£º 'Take your positions and get ready, for the sword devours those around you.'
24Jr 46:15 Why will your warriors be laid low? They cannot stand, for the LORD will push them down.
24Jr 46:16 They will stumble repeatedly; they will fall over each other. They will say, 'Get up, let us go back to our own people and our native lands, away from the sword of the oppressor.'
24Jr 46:17 There they will exclaim, 'Pharaoh king of Egypt is only a loud noise; he has missed his opportunity.'
24Jr 46:18 "As surely as I live," declares the King, whose name is the LORD Almighty, "one will come who is like Tabor among the mountains, like Carmel by the sea.
24Jr 46:19 Pack your belongings for exile, you who live in Egypt, for Memphis will be laid waste and lie in ruins without inhabitant.
24Jr 46:20 "Egypt is a beautiful heifer, but a gadfly is coming against her from the north.
24Jr 46:21 The mercenaries in her ranks are like fattened calves. They too will turn and flee together, they will not stand their ground, for the day of disaster is coming upon them, the time for them to be punished.
24Jr 46:22 Egypt will hiss like a fleeing serpent as the enemy advances in force; they will come against her with axes, like men who cut down trees.
24Jr 46:23 They will chop down her forest," declares the LORD, "dense though it be. They are more numerous than locusts, they cannot be counted.
24Jr 46:24 The Daughter of Egypt will be put to shame, handed over to the people of the north."
24Jr 46:25 The LORD Almighty, the God of Israel, says£º "I am about to bring punishment on Amon god of Thebes, on Pharaoh, on Egypt and her gods and her kings, and on those who rely on Pharaoh.
24Jr 46:26 I will hand them over to those who seek their lives, to Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon and his officers. Later, however, Egypt will be inhabited as in times past," declares the LORD.
24Jr 46:27 "Do not fear, O Jacob my servant; do not be dismayed, O Israel. I will surely save you out of a distant place, your descendants from the land of their exile. Jacob will again have peace and security, and no one will make him afraid.
24Jr 46:28 Do not fear, O Jacob my servant, for I am with you," declares the LORD. "Though I completely destroy all the nations among which I scatter you, I will not completely destroy you. I will discipline you but only with justice; I will not let you go entirely unpunished."
24Jr 47:1 This is the word of the LORD that came to Jeremiah the prophet concerning the Philistines before Pharaoh attacked Gaza£º
24Jr 47:2 This is what the LORD says£º "See how the waters are rising in the north; they will become an overflowing torrent. They will overflow the land and everything in it, the towns and those who live in them. The people will cry out; all who dwell in the land will wail
24Jr 47:3 at the sound of the hoofs of galloping steeds, at the noise of enemy chariots and the rumble of their wheels. Fathers will not turn to help their children; their hands will hang limp.
24Jr 47:4 For the day has come to destroy all the Philistines and to cut off all survivors who could help Tyre and Sidon. The LORD is about to destroy the Philistines, the remnant from the coasts of Caphtor.
24Jr 47:5 Gaza will shave her head in mourning; Ashkelon will be silenced. O remnant on the plain, how long will you cut yourselves?
24Jr 47:6 "'Ah, sword of the LORD,' you cry,'how long till you rest? Return to your scabbard; cease and be still.'
24Jr 47:7 But how can it rest when the LORD has commanded it, when he has ordered it to attack Ashkelon and the coast?"
24Jr 48:1 Concerning Moab£º This is what the LORD Almighty, the God of Israel, says£º "Woe to Nebo, for it will be ruined. Kiriathaim will be disgraced and captured; the stronghold will be disgraced and shattered.
24Jr 48:2 Moab will be praised no more; in Heshbon men will plot her downfall£º 'Come, let us put an end to that nation.' You too, O Madmen, will be silenced; the sword will pursue you.
24Jr 48:3 Listen to the cries from Horonaim, cries of great havoc and destruction.
24Jr 48:4 Moab will be broken; her little ones will cry out.
24Jr 48:5 They go up the way to Luhith, weeping bitterly as they go; on the road down to Horonaim anguished cries over the destruction are heard.
24Jr 48:6 Flee! Run for your lives; become like a bush in the desert.
24Jr 48:7 Since you trust in your deeds and riches, you too will be taken captive, and Chemosh will go into exile, together with his priests and officials.
24Jr 48:8 The destroyer will come against every town, and not a town will escape. The valley will be ruined and the plateau destroyed, because the LORD has spoken.
24Jr 48:9 Put salt on Moab, for she will be laid waste; her towns will become desolate, with no one to live in them.
24Jr 48:10 "A curse on him who is lax in doing the LORD'S work! A curse on him who keeps his sword from bloodshed!
24Jr 48:11 "Moab has been at rest from youth, like wine left on its dregs, not poured from one jar to another--she has not gone into exile. So she tastes as she did, and her aroma is unchanged.
24Jr 48:12 But days are coming," declares the LORD, "when I will send men who pour from jars, and they will pour her out; they will empty her jars and smash her jugs.
24Jr 48:13 Then Moab will be ashamed of Chemosh, as the house of Israel was ashamed when they trusted in Bethel.
24Jr 48:14 "How can you say, 'We are warriors, men valiant in battle'?
24Jr 48:15 Moab will be destroyed and her towns invaded; her finest young men will go down in the slaughter," declares the King, whose name is the LORD Almighty.
24Jr 48:16 "The fall of Moab is at hand; her calamity will come quickly.
24Jr 48:17 Mourn for her, all who live around her, all who know her fame; say, 'How broken is the mighty scepter, how broken the glorious staff!'
24Jr 48:18 "Come down from your glory and sit on the parched ground, O inhabitants of the Daughter of Dibon, for he who destroys Moab will come up against you and ruin your fortified cities.
24Jr 48:19 Stand by the road and watch, you who live in Aroer. Ask the man fleeing and the woman escaping, ask them, 'What has happened?'
24Jr 48:20 Moab is disgraced, for she is shattered. Wail and cry out! Announce by the Arnon that Moab is destroyed.
24Jr 48:21 Judgment has come to the plateau--to Holon, Jahzah and Mephaath,
24Jr 48:22 to Dibon, Nebo and Beth Diblathaim,
24Jr 48:23 to Kiriathaim, Beth Gamul and Beth Meon,
24Jr 48:24 to Kerioth and Bozrah--to all the towns of Moab, far and near.
24Jr 48:25 Moab's horn is cut off; her arm is broken," declares the LORD.
24Jr 48:26 "Make her drunk, for she has defied the LORD. Let Moab wallow in her vomit; let her be an object of ridicule.
24Jr 48:27 Was not Israel the object of your ridicule? Was she caught among thieves, that you shake your head in scorn whenever you speak of her?
24Jr 48:28 Abandon your towns and dwell among the rocks, you who live in Moab. Be like a dove that makes its nest at the mouth of a cave.
24Jr 48:29 "We have heard of Moab's pride--her overweening pride and conceit, her pride and arrogance and the haughtiness of her heart.
24Jr 48:30 I know her insolence but it is futile," declares the LORD, "and her boasts accomplish nothing.
24Jr 48:31 Therefore I wail over Moab, for all Moab I cry out, I moan for the men of Kir Hareseth.
24Jr 48:32 I weep for you, as Jazer weeps, O vines of Sibmah. Your branches spread as far as the sea; they reached as far as the sea of Jazer. The destroyer has fallen on your ripened fruit and grapes.
24Jr 48:33 Joy and gladness are gone from the orchards and fields of Moab. I have stopped the flow of wine from the presses; no one treads them with shouts of joy. Although there are shouts, they are not shouts of joy.
24Jr 48:34 "The sound of their cry rises from Heshbon to Elealeh and Jahaz, from Zoar as far as Horonaim and Eglath Shelishiyah, for even the waters of Nimrim are dried up.
24Jr 48:35 In Moab I will put an end to those who make offerings on the high places and burn incense to their gods," declares the LORD.
24Jr 48:36 "So my heart laments for Moab like a flute; it laments like a flute for the men of Kir Hareseth. The wealth they acquired is gone.
24Jr 48:37 Every head is shaved and every beard cut off; every hand is slashed and every waist is covered with sackcloth.
24Jr 48:38 On all the roofs in Moab and in the public squares there is nothing but mourning, for I have broken Moab like a jar that no one wants," declares the LORD.
24Jr 48:39 "How shattered she is! How they wail! How Moab turns her back in shame! Moab has become an object of ridicule, an object of horror to all those around her."
24Jr 48:40 This is what the LORD says£º "Look! An eagle is swooping down, spreading its wings over Moab.
24Jr 48:41 Kerioth will be captured and the strongholds taken. In that day the hearts of Moab's warriors will be like the heart of a woman in labor.
24Jr 48:42 Moab will be destroyed as a nation because she defied the LORD.
24Jr 48:43 Terror and pit and snare await you, O people of Moab," declares the LORD.
24Jr 48:44 "Whoever flees from the terror will fall into a pit, whoever climbs out of the pit will be caught in a snare; for I will bring upon Moab the year of her punishment," declares the LORD.
24Jr 48:45 "In the shadow of Heshbon the fugitives stand helpless, for a fire has gone out from Heshbon, a blaze from the midst of Sihon; it burns the foreheads of Moab, the skulls of the noisy boasters.
24Jr 48:46 Woe to you, O Moab! The people of Chemosh are destroyed; your sons are taken into exile and your daughters into captivity.
24Jr 48:47 "Yet I will restore the fortunes of Moab in days to come," declares the LORD. Here ends the judgment on Moab.
24Jr 49:1 Concerning the Ammonites£º This is what the LORD says£º "Has Israel no sons? Has she no heirs? Why then has Molech taken possession of Gad? Why do his people live in its towns?
24Jr 49:2 But the days are coming," declares the LORD, "when I will sound the battle cry against Rabbah of the Ammonites; it will become a mound of ruins, and its surrounding villages will be set on fire. Then Israel will drive out those who drove her out," says the LORD.
24Jr 49:3 "Wail, O Heshbon, for Ai is destroyed! Cry out, O inhabitants of Rabbah! Put on sackcloth and mourn; rush here and there inside the walls, for Molech will go into exile, together with his priests and officials.
24Jr 49:4 Why do you boast of your valleys, boast of your valleys so fruitful? O unfaithful daughter, you trust in your riches and say, 'Who will attack me?'
24Jr 49:5 I will bring terror on you from all those around you," declares the Lord, the LORD Almighty. "Every one of you will be driven away, and no one will gather the fugitives.
24Jr 49:6 "Yet afterward, I will restore the fortunes of the Ammonites," declares the LORD.
24Jr 49:7 Concerning Edom£º This is what the LORD Almighty says£º "Is there no longer wisdom in Teman? Has counsel perished from the prudent? Has their wisdom decayed?
24Jr 49:8 Turn and flee, hide in deep caves, you who live in Dedan, for I will bring disaster on Esau at the time I punish him.
24Jr 49:9 If grape pickers came to you, would they not leave a few grapes? If thieves came during the night, would they not steal only as much as they wanted?
24Jr 49:10 But I will strip Esau bare; I will uncover his hiding places, so that he cannot conceal himself. His children, relatives and neighbors will perish, and he will be no more.
24Jr 49:11 Leave your orphans; I will protect their lives. Your widows too can trust in me."
24Jr 49:12 This is what the LORD says£º "If those who do not deserve to drink the cup must drink it, why should you go unpunished? You will not go unpunished, but must drink it.
24Jr 49:13 I swear by myself," declares the LORD, "that Bozrah will become a ruin and an object of horror, of reproach and of cursing; and all its towns will be in ruins forever."
24Jr 49:14 I have heard a message from the LORD£º An envoy was sent to the nations to say, "Assemble yourselves to attack it! Rise up for battle!"
24Jr 49:15 "Now I will make you small among the nations, despised among men.
24Jr 49:16 The terror you inspire and the pride of your heart have deceived you, you who live in the clefts of the rocks, who occupy the heights of the hill. Though you build your nest as high as the eagle's, from there I will bring you down," declares the LORD.
24Jr 49:17 "Edom will become an object of horror; all who pass by will be appalled and will scoff because of all its wounds.
24Jr 49:18 As Sodom and Gomorrah were overthrown, along with their neighboring towns," says the LORD, "so no one will live there; no man will dwell in it.
24Jr 49:19 "Like a lion coming up from Jordan's thickets to a rich pastureland, I will chase Edom from its land in an instant. Who is the chosen one I will appoint for this? Who is like me and who can challenge me? And what shepherd can stand against me?"
24Jr 49:20 Therefore, hear what the LORD has planned against Edom, what he has purposed against those who live in Teman£º The young of the flock will be dragged away; he will completely destroy their pasture because of them.
24Jr 49:21 At the sound of their fall the earth will tremble; their cry will resound to the Red Sea.
24Jr 49:22 Look! An eagle will soar and swoop down, spreading its wings over Bozrah. In that day the hearts of Edom's warriors will be like the heart of a woman in labor.
24Jr 49:23 Concerning Damascus£º "Hamath and Arpad are dismayed, for they have heard bad news. They are disheartened, troubled like the restless sea.
24Jr 49:24 Damascus has become feeble, she has turned to flee and panic has gripped her; anguish and pain have seized her, pain like that of a woman in labor.
24Jr 49:25 Why has the city of renown not been abandoned, the town in which I delight?
24Jr 49:26 Surely, her young men will fall in the streets; all her soldiers will be silenced in that day," declares the LORD Almighty.
24Jr 49:27 "I will set fire to the walls of Damascus; it will consume the fortresses of Ben-Hadad."
24Jr 49:28 Concerning Kedar and the kingdoms of Hazor, which Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon attacked£º This is what the LORD says£º "Arise, and attack Kedar and destroy the people of the East.
24Jr 49:29 Their tents and their flocks will be taken; their shelters will be carried off with all their goods and camels. Men will shout to them, 'Terror on every side!'
24Jr 49:30 "Flee quickly away! Stay in deep caves, you who live in Hazor," declares the LORD. "Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon has plotted against you; he has devised a plan against you.
24Jr 49:31 "Arise and attack a nation at ease, which lives in confidence," declares the LORD, "a nation that has neither gates nor bars; its people live alone.
24Jr 49:32 Their camels will become plunder, and their large herds will be booty. I will scatter to the winds those who are in distant places and will bring disaster on them from every side," declares the LORD.
24Jr 49:33 "Hazor will become a haunt of jackals, a desolate place forever. No one will live there; no man will dwell in it."
24Jr 49:34 This is the word of the LORD that came to Jeremiah the prophet concerning Elam, early in the reign of Zedekiah king of Judah£º
24Jr 49:35 This is what the LORD Almighty says£º "See, I will break the bow of Elam, the mainstay of their might.
24Jr 49:36 I will bring against Elam the four winds from the four quarters of the heavens; I will scatter them to the four winds, and there will not be a nation where Elam's exiles do not go.
24Jr 49:37 I will shatter Elam before their foes, before those who seek their lives; I will bring disaster upon them, even my fierce anger," declares the LORD. "I will pursue them with the sword until I have made an end of them.
24Jr 49:38 I will set my throne in Elam and destroy her king and officials," declares the LORD.
24Jr 49:39 "Yet I will restore the fortunes of Elam in days to come," declares the LORD.
24Jr 50:1 This is the word the LORD spoke through Jeremiah the prophet concerning Babylon and the land of the Babylonians£º
24Jr 50:2 "Announce and proclaim among the nations, lift up a banner and proclaim it; keep nothing back, but say, 'Babylon will be captured; Bel will be put to shame, Marduk filled with terror. Her images will be put to shame and her idols filled with terror.'
24Jr 50:3 A nation from the north will attack her and lay waste her land. No one will live in it; both men and animals will flee away.
24Jr 50:4 "In those days, at that time," declares the LORD, "the people of Israel and the people of Judah together will go in tears to seek the LORD their God.
24Jr 50:5 They will ask the way to Zion and turn their faces toward it. They will come and bind themselves to the LORD in an everlasting covenant that will not be forgotten.
24Jr 50:6 "My people have been lost sheep; their shepherds have led them astray and caused them to roam on the mountains. They wandered over mountain and hill and forgot their own resting place.
24Jr 50:7 Whoever found them devoured them; their enemies said, 'We are not guilty, for they sinned against the LORD, their true pasture, the LORD, the hope of their fathers.'
24Jr 50:8 "Flee out of Babylon; leave the land of the Babylonians, and be like the goats that lead the flock.
24Jr 50:9 For I will stir up and bring against Babylon an alliance of great nations from the land of the north. They will take up their positions against her, and from the north she will be captured. Their arrows will be like skilled warriors who do not return empty-handed.
24Jr 50:10 So Babylonia will be plundered; all who plunder her will have their fill," declares the LORD.
24Jr 50:11 "Because you rejoice and are glad, you who pillage my inheritance, because you frolic like a heifer threshing grain and neigh like stallions,
24Jr 50:12 your mother will be greatly ashamed; she who gave you birth will be disgraced. She will be the least of the nations--a wilderness, a dry land, a desert.
24Jr 50:13 Because of the LORD'S anger she will not be inhabited but will be completely desolate. All who pass Babylon will be horrified and scoff because of all her wounds.
24Jr 50:14 "Take up your positions around Babylon, all you who draw the bow. Shoot at her! Spare no arrows, for she has sinned against the LORD.
24Jr 50:15 Shout against her on every side! She surrenders, her towers fall, her walls are torn down. Since this is the vengeance of the LORD, take vengeance on her; do to her as she has done to others.
24Jr 50:16 Cut off from Babylon the sower, and the reaper with his sickle at harvest. Because of the sword of the oppressor let everyone return to his own people, let everyone flee to his own land.
24Jr 50:17 "Israel is a scattered flock that lions have chased away. The first to devour him was the king of Assyria; the last to crush his bones was Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon."
24Jr 50:18 Therefore this is what the LORD Almighty, the God of Israel, says£º "I will punish the king of Babylon and his land as I punished the king of Assyria.
24Jr 50:19 But I will bring Israel back to his own pasture and he will graze on Carmel and Bashan; his appetite will be satisfied on the hills of Ephraim and Gilead.
24Jr 50:20 In those days, at that time," declares the LORD, "search will be made for Israel's guilt, but there will be none, and for the sins of Judah, but none will be found, for I will forgive the remnant I spare.
24Jr 50:21 "Attack the land of Merathaim and those who live in Pekod. Pursue, kill and completely destroy them," declares the LORD. "Do everything I have commanded you.
24Jr 50:22 The noise of battle is in the land, the noise of great destruction!
24Jr 50:23 How broken and shattered is the hammer of the whole earth! How desolate is Babylon among the nations!
24Jr 50:24 I set a trap for you, O Babylon, and you were caught before you knew it; you were found and captured because you opposed the LORD.
24Jr 50:25 The LORD has opened his arsenal and brought out the weapons of his wrath, for the Sovereign LORD Almighty has work to do in the land of the Babylonians.
24Jr 50:26 Come against her from afar. Break open her granaries; pile her up like heaps of grain. Completely destroy her and leave her no remnant.
24Jr 50:27 Kill all her young bulls; let them go down to the slaughter! Woe to them! For their day has come, the time for them to be punished.
24Jr 50:28 Listen to the fugitives and refugees from Babylon declaring in Zion how the LORD our God has taken vengeance, vengeance for his temple.
24Jr 50:29 "Summon archers against Babylon, all those who draw the bow. Encamp all around her; let no one escape. Repay her for her deeds; do to her as she has done. For she has defied the LORD, the Holy One of Israel.
24Jr 50:30 Therefore, her young men will fall in the streets; all her soldiers will be silenced in that day," declares the LORD.
24Jr 50:31 "See, I am against you, O arrogant one," declares the Lord, the LORD Almighty, "for your day has come, the time for you to be punished.
24Jr 50:32 The arrogant one will stumble and fall and no one will help her up; I will kindle a fire in her towns that will consume all who are around her."
24Jr 50:33 This is what the LORD Almighty says£º "The people of Israel are oppressed, and the people of Judah as well. All their captors hold them fast, refusing to let them go.
24Jr 50:34 Yet their Redeemer is strong; the LORD Almighty is his name. He will vigorously defend their cause so that he may bring rest to their land, but unrest to those who live in Babylon.
24Jr 50:35 "A sword against the Babylonians!" declares the LORD--"against those who live in Babylon and against her officials and wise men!
24Jr 50:36 A sword against her false prophets! They will become fools. A sword against her warriors! They will be filled with terror.
24Jr 50:37 A sword against her horses and chariots and all the foreigners in her ranks! They will become women. A sword against her treasures! They will be plundered.
24Jr 50:38 A drought on her waters! They will dry up. For it is a land of idols, idols that will go mad with terror.
24Jr 50:39 "So desert creatures and hyenas will live there, and there the owl will dwell. It will never again be inhabited or lived in from generation to generation.
24Jr 50:40 As God overthrew Sodom and Gomorrah along with their neighboring towns," declares the LORD, "so no one will live there; no man will dwell in it.
24Jr 50:41 "Look! An army is coming from the north; a great nation and many kings are being stirred up from the ends of the earth.
24Jr 50:42 They are armed with bows and spears; they are cruel and without mercy. They sound like the roaring sea as they ride on their horses; they come like men in battle formation to attack you, O Daughter of Babylon.
24Jr 50:43 The king of Babylon has heard reports about them, and his hands hang limp. Anguish has gripped him, pain like that of a woman in labor.
24Jr 50:44 Like a lion coming up from Jordan's thickets to a rich pastureland, I will chase Babylon from its land in an instant. Who is the chosen one I will appoint for this? Who is like me and who can challenge me? And what shepherd can stand against me?"
24Jr 50:45 Therefore, hear what the LORD has planned against Babylon, what he has purposed against the land of the Babylonians£º The young of the flock will be dragged away; he will completely destroy their pasture because of them.
24Jr 50:46 At the sound of Babylon's capture the earth will tremble; its cry will resound among the nations.
24Jr 51:1 This is what the LORD says£º "See, I will stir up the spirit of a destroyer against Babylon and the people of Leb Kamai.
24Jr 51:2 I will send foreigners to Babylon to winnow her and to devastate her land; they will oppose her on every side in the day of her disaster.
24Jr 51:3 Let not the archer string his bow, nor let him put on his armor. Do not spare her young men; completely destroy her army.
24Jr 51:4 They will fall down slain in Babylon, fatally wounded in her streets.
24Jr 51:5 For Israel and Judah have not been forsaken by their God, the LORD Almighty, though their land is full of guilt before the Holy One of Israel.
24Jr 51:6 "Flee from Babylon! Run for your lives! Do not be destroyed because of her sins. It is time for the LORD'S vengeance; he will pay her what she deserves.
24Jr 51:7 Babylon was a gold cup in the LORD'S hand; she made the whole earth drunk. The nations drank her wine; therefore they have now gone mad.
24Jr 51:8 Babylon will suddenly fall and be broken. Wail over her! Get balm for her pain; perhaps she can be healed.
24Jr 51:9 "'We would have healed Babylon, but she cannot be healed; let us leave her and each go to his own land, for her judgment reaches to the skies, it rises as high as the clouds.'
24Jr 51:10 "'The LORD has vindicated us; come, let us tell in Zion what the LORD our God has done.'
24Jr 51:11 "Sharpen the arrows, take up the shields! The LORD has stirred up the kings of the Medes, because his purpose is to destroy Babylon. The LORD will take vengeance, vengeance for his temple.
24Jr 51:12 Lift up a banner against the walls of Babylon! Reinforce the guard, station the watchmen, prepare an ambush! The LORD will carry out his purpose, his decree against the people of Babylon.
24Jr 51:13 You who live by many waters and are rich in treasures, your end has come, the time for you to be cut off.
24Jr 51:14 The LORD Almighty has sworn by himself£º I will surely fill you with men, as with a swarm of locusts, and they will shout in triumph over you.
24Jr 51:15 "He made the earth by his power; he founded the world by his wisdom and stretched out the heavens by his understanding.
24Jr 51:16 When he thunders, the waters in the heavens roar; he makes clouds rise from the ends of the earth. He sends lightning with the rain and brings out the wind from his storehouses.
24Jr 51:17 "Every man is senseless and without knowledge; every goldsmith is shamed by his idols. His images are a fraud; they have no breath in them.
24Jr 51:18 They are worthless, the objects of mockery; when their judgment comes, they will perish.
24Jr 51:19 He who is the Portion of Jacob is not like these, for he is the Maker of all things, including the tribe of his inheritance--the LORD Almighty is his name.
24Jr 51:20 "You are my war club, my weapon for battle--with you I shatter nations, with you I destroy kingdoms,
24Jr 51:21 with you I shatter horse and rider, with you I shatter chariot and driver,
24Jr 51:22 with you I shatter man and woman, with you I shatter old man and youth, with you I shatter young man and maiden,
24Jr 51:23 with you I shatter shepherd and flock, with you I shatter farmer and oxen, with you I shatter governors and officials.
24Jr 51:24 "Before your eyes I will repay Babylon and all who live in Babylonia for all the wrong they have done in Zion," declares the LORD.
24Jr 51:25 "I am against you, O destroying mountain, you who destroy the whole earth," declares the LORD. "I will stretch out my hand against you, roll you off the cliffs, and make you a burned-out mountain.
24Jr 51:26 No rock will be taken from you for a cornerstone, nor any stone for a foundation, for you will be desolate forever," declares the LORD.
24Jr 51:27 "Lift up a banner in the land! Blow the trumpet among the nations! Prepare the nations for battle against her; summon against her these kingdoms£º Ararat, Minni and Ashkenaz. Appoint a commander against her; send up horses like a swarm of locusts.
24Jr 51:28 Prepare the nations for battle against her--the kings of the Medes, their governors and all their officials, and all the countries they rule.
24Jr 51:29 The land trembles and writhes, for the LORD'S purposes against Babylon stand--to lay waste the land of Babylon so that no one will live there.
24Jr 51:30 Babylon's warriors have stopped fighting; they remain in their strongholds. Their strength is exhausted; they have become like women. Her dwellings are set on fire; the bars of her gates are broken.
24Jr 51:31 One courier follows another and messenger follows messenger to announce to the king of Babylon that his entire city is captured,
24Jr 51:32 the river crossings seized, the marshes set on fire, and the soldiers terrified."
24Jr 51:33 This is what the LORD Almighty, the God of Israel, says£º "The Daughter of Babylon is like a threshing floor at the time it is trampled; the time to harvest her will soon come."
24Jr 51:34 "Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon has devoured us, he has thrown us into confusion, he has made us an empty jar. Like a serpent he has swallowed us and filled his stomach with our delicacies, and then has spewed us out.
24Jr 51:35 May the violence done to our flesh be upon Babylon," say the inhabitants of Zion. "May our blood be on those who live in Babylonia," says Jerusalem.
24Jr 51:36 Therefore, this is what the LORD says£º "See, I will defend your cause and avenge you; I will dry up her sea and make her springs dry.
24Jr 51:37 Babylon will be a heap of ruins, a haunt of jackals, an object of horror and scorn, a place where no one lives.
24Jr 51:38 Her people all roar like young lions, they growl like lion cubs.
24Jr 51:39 But while they are aroused, I will set out a feast for them and make them drunk, so that they shout with laughter--then sleep forever and not awake," declares the LORD.
24Jr 51:40 "I will bring them down like lambs to the slaughter, like rams and goats.
24Jr 51:41 "How Sheshach will be captured, the boast of the whole earth seized! What a horror Babylon will be among the nations!
24Jr 51:42 The sea will rise over Babylon; its roaring waves will cover her.
24Jr 51:43 Her towns will be desolate, a dry and desert land, a land where no one lives, through which no man travels.
24Jr 51:44 I will punish Bel in Babylon and make him spew out what he has swallowed. The nations will no longer stream to him. And the wall of Babylon will fall.
24Jr 51:45 "Come out of her, my people! Run for your lives! Run from the fierce anger of the LORD.
24Jr 51:46 Do not lose heart or be afraid when rumors are heard in the land; one rumor comes this year, another the next, rumors of violence in the land and of ruler against ruler.
24Jr 51:47 For the time will surely come when I will punish the idols of Babylon; her whole land will be disgraced and her slain will all lie fallen within her.
24Jr 51:48 Then heaven and earth and all that is in them will shout for joy over Babylon, for out of the north destroyers will attack her," declares the LORD.
24Jr 51:49 "Babylon must fall because of Israel's slain, just as the slain in all the earth have fallen because of Babylon.
24Jr 51:50 You who have escaped the sword, leave and do not linger! Remember the LORD in a distant land, and think on Jerusalem."
24Jr 51:51 "We are disgraced, for we have been insulted and shame covers our faces, because foreigners have entered the holy places of the LORD'S house."
24Jr 51:52 "But days are coming," declares the LORD, "when I will punish her idols, and throughout her land the wounded will groan.
24Jr 51:53 Even if Babylon reaches the sky and fortifies her lofty stronghold, I will send destroyers against her," declares the LORD.
24Jr 51:54 "The sound of a cry comes from Babylon, the sound of great destruction from the land of the Babylonians.
24Jr 51:55 The LORD will destroy Babylon; he will silence her noisy din. Waves of enemies will rage like great waters; the roar of their voices will resound.
24Jr 51:56 A destroyer will come against Babylon; her warriors will be captured, and their bows will be broken. For the LORD is a God of retribution; he will repay in full.
24Jr 51:57 I will make her officials and wise men drunk, her governors, officers and warriors as well; they will sleep forever and not awake," declares the King, whose name is the LORD Almighty.
24Jr 51:58 This is what the LORD Almighty says£º "Babylon's thick wall will be leveled and her high gates set on fire; the peoples exhaust themselves for nothing, the nations' labor is only fuel for the flames."
24Jr 51:59 This is the message Jeremiah gave to the staff officer Seraiah son of Neriah, the son of Mahseiah, when he went to Babylon with Zedekiah king of Judah in the fourth year of his reign.
24Jr 51:60 Jeremiah had written on a scroll about all the disasters that would come upon Babylon--all that had been recorded concerning Babylon.
24Jr 51:61 He said to Seraiah, "When you get to Babylon, see that you read all these words aloud.
24Jr 51:62 Then say, 'O LORD, you have said you will destroy this place, so that neither man nor animal will live in it; it will be desolate forever.'
24Jr 51:63 When you finish reading this scroll, tie a stone to it and throw it into the Euphrates.
24Jr 51:64 Then say, 'So will Babylon sink to rise no more because of the disaster I will bring upon her. And her people will fall.'" The words of Jeremiah end here.
24Jr 52:1 Zedekiah was twenty-one years old when he became king, and he reigned in Jerusalem eleven years. His mother's name was Hamutal daughter of Jeremiah; she was from Libnah.
24Jr 52:2 He did evil in the eyes of the LORD, just as Jehoiakim had done.
24Jr 52:3 It was because of the LORD'S anger that all this happened to Jerusalem and Judah, and in the end he thrust them from his presence. Now Zedekiah rebelled against the king of Babylon.
24Jr 52:4 So in the ninth year of Zedekiah's reign, on the tenth day of the tenth month, Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon marched against Jerusalem with his whole army. They camped outside the city and built siege works all around it.
24Jr 52:5 The city was kept under siege until the eleventh year of King Zedekiah.
24Jr 52:6 By the ninth day of the fourth month the famine in the city had become so severe that there was no food for the people to eat.
24Jr 52:7 Then the city wall was broken through, and the whole army fled. They left the city at night through the gate between the two walls near the king's garden, though the Babylonians were surrounding the city. They fled toward the Arabah,
24Jr 52:8 but the Babylonian army pursued King Zedekiah and overtook him in the plains of Jericho. All his soldiers were separated from him and scattered,
24Jr 52:9 and he was captured. He was taken to the king of Babylon at Riblah in the land of Hamath, where he pronounced sentence on him.
24Jr 52:10 There at Riblah the king of Babylon slaughtered the sons of Zedekiah before his eyes; he also killed all the officials of Judah.
24Jr 52:11 Then he put out Zedekiah's eyes, bound him with bronze shackles and took him to Babylon, where he put him in prison till the day of his death.
24Jr 52:12 On the tenth day of the fifth month, in the nineteenth year of Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon, Nebuzaradan commander of the imperial guard, who served the king of Babylon, came to Jerusalem.
24Jr 52:13 He set fire to the temple of the LORD, the royal palace and all the houses of Jerusalem. Every important building he burned down.
24Jr 52:14 The whole Babylonian army under the commander of the imperial guard broke down all the walls around Jerusalem.
24Jr 52:15 Nebuzaradan the commander of the guard carried into exile some of the poorest people and those who remained in the city, along with the rest of the craftsmen and those who had gone over to the king of Babylon.
24Jr 52:16 But Nebuzaradan left behind the rest of the poorest people of the land to work the vineyards and fields.
24Jr 52:17 The Babylonians broke up the bronze pillars, the movable stands and the bronze Sea that were at the temple of the LORD and they carried all the bronze to Babylon.
24Jr 52:18 They also took away the pots, shovels, wick trimmers, sprinkling bowls, dishes and all the bronze articles used in the temple service.
24Jr 52:19 The commander of the imperial guard took away the basins, censers, sprinkling bowls, pots, lampstands, dishes and bowls used for drink offerings--all that were made of pure gold or silver.
24Jr 52:20 The bronze from the two pillars, the Sea and the twelve bronze bulls under it, and the movable stands, which King Solomon had made for the temple of the LORD, was more than could be weighed.
24Jr 52:21 Each of the pillars was eighteen cubits high and twelve cubits in circumference; each was four fingers thick, and hollow.
24Jr 52:22 The bronze capital on top of the one pillar was five cubits high and was decorated with a network and pomegranates of bronze all around. The other pillar, with its pomegranates, was similar.
24Jr 52:23 There were ninety-six pomegranates on the sides; the total number of pomegranates above the surrounding network was a hundred.
24Jr 52:24 The commander of the guard took as prisoners Seraiah the chief priest, Zephaniah the priest next in rank and the three doorkeepers.
24Jr 52:25 Of those still in the city, he took the officer in charge of the fighting men, and seven royal advisers. He also took the secretary who was chief officer in charge of conscripting the people of the land and sixty of his men who were found in the city.
24Jr 52:26 Nebuzaradan the commander took them all and brought them to the king of Babylon at Riblah.
24Jr 52:27 There at Riblah, in the land of Hamath, the king had them executed. So Judah went into captivity, away from her land.
24Jr 52:28 This is the number of the people Nebuchadnezzar carried into exile£º in the seventh year, 3,023 Jews;
24Jr 52:29 in Nebuchadnezzar's eighteenth year, 832 people from Jerusalem;
24Jr 52:30 in his twenty-third year, 745 Jews taken into exile by Nebuzaradan the commander of the imperial guard. There were 4,600 people in all.
24Jr 52:31 In the thirty-seventh year of the exile of Jehoiachin king of Judah, in the year Evil-Merodach became king of Babylon, he released Jehoiachin king of Judah and freed him from prison on the twenty-fifth day of the twelfth month.
24Jr 52:32 He spoke kindly to him and gave him a seat of honor higher than those of the other kings who were with him in Babylon.
24Jr 52:33 So Jehoiachin put aside his prison clothes and for the rest of his life ate regularly at the king's table.
24Jr 52:34 Day by day the king of Babylon gave Jehoiachin a regular allowance as long as he lived, till the day of his death.
