26Ezk 4:11 Also measure out a sixth of a hin of water and drink it at set times.
26Ezk 4:12 Eat the food as you would a barley cake; bake it in the sight of the people, using human excrement for fuel."
26Ezk 4:13 The LORD said, "In this way the people of Israel will eat defiled food among the nations where I will drive them."
26Ezk 4:14 Then I said, "Not so, Sovereign LORD! I have never defiled myself. From my youth until now I have never eaten anything found dead or torn by wild animals. No unclean meat has ever entered my mouth."
