26Ezk 9:9 He answered me, "The sin of the house of Israel and Judah is exceedingly great; the land is full of bloodshed and the city is full of injustice. They say, 'The LORD has forsaken the land; the LORD does not see.'
26Ezk 9:10 So I will not look on them with pity or spare them, but I will bring down on their own heads what they have done."
26Ezk 9:11 Then the man in linen with the writing kit at his side brought back word, saying, "I have done as you commanded."
26Ezk 10:1 I looked, and I saw the likeness of a throne of sapphire above the expanse that was over the heads of the cherubim.
26Ezk 10:2 The LORD said to the man clothed in linen, "Go in among the wheels beneath the cherubim. Fill your hands with burning coals from among the cherubim and scatter them over the city." And as I watched, he went in.
26Ezk 10:3 Now the cherubim were standing on the south side of the temple when the man went in, and a cloud filled the inner court.
26Ezk 10:4 Then the glory of the LORD rose from above the cherubim and moved to the threshold of the temple. The cloud filled the temple, and the court was full of the radiance of the glory of the LORD.
26Ezk 10:5 The sound of the wings of the cherubim could be heard as far away as the outer court, like the voice of God Almighty when he speaks.
26Ezk 10:6 When the LORD commanded the man in linen, "Take fire from among the wheels, from among the cherubim," the man went in and stood beside a wheel.
26Ezk 10:7 Then one of the cherubim reached out his hand to the fire that was among them. He took up some of it and put it into the hands of the man in linen, who took it and went out.
26Ezk 10:8 (Under the wings of the cherubim could be seen what looked like the hands of a man.)
