26Ezk 11:7 "Therefore this is what the Sovereign LORD says£º The bodies you have thrown there are the meat and this city is the pot, but I will drive you out of it.
26Ezk 11:8 You fear the sword, and the sword is what I will bring against you, declares the Sovereign LORD.
26Ezk 11:9 I will drive you out of the city and hand you over to foreigners and inflict punishment on you.
26Ezk 11:10 You will fall by the sword, and I will execute judgment on you at the borders of Israel. Then you will know that I am the LORD.
26Ezk 11:11 This city will not be a pot for you, nor will you be the meat in it; I will execute judgment on you at the borders of Israel.
26Ezk 11:12 And you will know that I am the LORD, for you have not followed my decrees or kept my laws but have conformed to the standards of the nations around you."
26Ezk 11:13 Now as I was prophesying, Pelatiah son of Benaiah died. Then I fell facedown and cried out in a loud voice, "Ah, Sovereign LORD! Will you completely destroy the remnant of Israel?"
26Ezk 11:14 The word of the LORD came to me£º
26Ezk 11:15 "Son of man, your brothers--your brothers who are your blood relatives and the whole house of Israel--are those of whom the people of Jerusalem have said, 'They are far away from the LORD; this land was given to us as our possession.'
26Ezk 11:16 "Therefore say£º 'This is what the Sovereign LORD says£º Although I sent them far away among the nations and scattered them among the countries, yet for a little while I have been a sanctuary for them in the countries where they have gone.'
26Ezk 11:17 "Therefore say£º 'This is what the Sovereign LORD says£º I will gather you from the nations and bring you back from the countries where you have been scattered, and I will give you back the land of Israel again.'
26Ezk 11:18 "They will return to it and remove all its vile images and detestable idols.
26Ezk 11:19 I will give them an undivided heart and put a new spirit in them; I will remove from them their heart of stone and give them a heart of flesh.
26Ezk 11:20 Then they will follow my decrees and be careful to keep my laws. They will be my people, and I will be their God.
26Ezk 11:21 But as for those whose hearts are devoted to their vile images and detestable idols, I will bring down on their own heads what they have done, declares the Sovereign LORD."
26Ezk 11:22 Then the cherubim, with the wheels beside them, spread their wings, and the glory of the God of Israel was above them.
26Ezk 11:23 The glory of the LORD went up from within the city and stopped above the mountain east of it.
26Ezk 11:24 The Spirit lifted me up and brought me to the exiles in Babylonia in the vision given by the Spirit of God. Then the vision I had seen went up from me,
26Ezk 11:25 and I told the exiles everything the LORD had shown me.
26Ezk 12:1 The word of the LORD came to me£º
26Ezk 12:2 "Son of man, you are living among a rebellious people. They have eyes to see but do not see and ears to hear but do not hear, for they are a rebellious people.
26Ezk 12:3 "Therefore, son of man, pack your belongings for exile and in the daytime, as they watch, set out and go from where you are to another place. Perhaps they will understand, though they are a rebellious house.
26Ezk 12:4 During the daytime, while they watch, bring out your belongings packed for exile. Then in the evening, while they are watching, go out like those who go into exile.
26Ezk 12:5 While they watch, dig through the wall and take your belongings out through it.
26Ezk 12:6 Put them on your shoulder as they are watching and carry them out at dusk. Cover your face so that you cannot see the land, for I have made you a sign to the house of Israel."
26Ezk 12:7 So I did as I was commanded. During the day I brought out my things packed for exile. Then in the evening I dug through the wall with my hands. I took my belongings out at dusk, carrying them on my shoulders while they watched.
26Ezk 12:8 In the morning the word of the LORD came to me£º
26Ezk 12:9 "Son of man, did not that rebellious house of Israel ask you, 'What are you doing?'
26Ezk 12:10 "Say to them, 'This is what the Sovereign LORD says£º This oracle concerns the prince in Jerusalem and the whole house of Israel who are there.'
26Ezk 12:11 Say to them, 'I am a sign to you.' "As I have done, so it will be done to them. They will go into exile as captives.
26Ezk 12:12 "The prince among them will put his things on his shoulder at dusk and leave, and a hole will be dug in the wall for him to go through. He will cover his face so that he cannot see the land.
26Ezk 12:13 I will spread my net for him, and he will be caught in my snare; I will bring him to Babylonia, the land of the Chaldeans, but he will not see it, and there he will die.
26Ezk 12:14 I will scatter to the winds all those around him--his staff and all his troops--and I will pursue them with drawn sword.
26Ezk 12:15 "They will know that I am the LORD, when I disperse them among the nations and scatter them through the countries.
26Ezk 12:16 But I will spare a few of them from the sword, famine and plague, so that in the nations where they go they may acknowledge all their detestable practices. Then they will know that I am the LORD."
26Ezk 12:17 The word of the LORD came to me£º
26Ezk 12:18 "Son of man, tremble as you eat your food, and shudder in fear as you drink your water.
26Ezk 12:19 Say to the people of the land£º 'This is what the Sovereign LORD says about those living in Jerusalem and in the land of Israel£º They will eat their food in anxiety and drink their water in despair, for their land will be stripped of everything in it because of the violence of all who live there.
26Ezk 12:20 The inhabited towns will be laid waste and the land will be desolate. Then you will know that I am the LORD.'"
26Ezk 12:21 The word of the LORD came to me£º
26Ezk 12:22 "Son of man, what is this proverb you have in the land of Israel£º 'The days go by and every vision comes to nothing'?
26Ezk 12:23 Say to them, 'This is what the Sovereign LORD says£º I am going to put an end to this proverb, and they will no longer quote it in Israel.' Say to them, 'The days are near when every vision will be fulfilled.
26Ezk 12:24 For there will be no more false visions or flattering divinations among the people of Israel.
26Ezk 12:25 But I the LORD will speak what I will, and it shall be fulfilled without delay. For in your days, you rebellious house, I will fulfill whatever I say, declares the Sovereign LORD.'"
26Ezk 12:26 The word of the LORD came to me£º
26Ezk 12:27 "Son of man, the house of Israel is saying, 'The vision he sees is for many years from now, and he prophesies about the distant future.'
26Ezk 12:28 "Therefore say to them, 'This is what the Sovereign LORD says£º None of my words will be delayed any longer; whatever I say will be fulfilled, declares the Sovereign LORD.'"
26Ezk 13:1 The word of the LORD came to me£º
26Ezk 13:2 "Son of man, prophesy against the prophets of Israel who are now prophesying. Say to those who prophesy out of their own imagination£º 'Hear the word of the LORD!
26Ezk 13:3 This is what the Sovereign LORD says£º Woe to the foolish prophets who follow their own spirit and have seen nothing!
26Ezk 13:4 Your prophets, O Israel, are like jackals among ruins.
26Ezk 13:5 You have not gone up to the breaks in the wall to repair it for the house of Israel so that it will stand firm in the battle on the day of the LORD.
26Ezk 13:6 Their visions are false and their divinations a lie. They say, "The LORD declares," when the LORD has not sent them; yet they expect their words to be fulfilled.
26Ezk 13:7 Have you not seen false visions and uttered lying divinations when you say, "The LORD declares," though I have not spoken?
26Ezk 13:8 "'Therefore this is what the Sovereign LORD says£º Because of your false words and lying visions, I am against you, declares the Sovereign LORD.
26Ezk 13:9 My hand will be against the prophets who see false visions and utter lying divinations. They will not belong to the council of my people or be listed in the records of the house of Israel, nor will they enter the land of Israel. Then you will know that I am the Sovereign LORD.
26Ezk 13:10 "'Because they lead my people astray, saying, "Peace," when there is no peace, and because, when a flimsy wall is built, they cover it with whitewash,
26Ezk 13:11 therefore tell those who cover it with whitewash that it is going to fall. Rain will come in torrents, and I will send hailstones hurtling down, and violent winds will burst forth.
26Ezk 13:12 When the wall collapses, will people not ask you, "Where is the whitewash you covered it with?"
26Ezk 13:13 "'Therefore this is what the Sovereign LORD says£º In my wrath I will unleash a violent wind, and in my anger hailstones and torrents of rain will fall with destructive fury.
26Ezk 13:14 I will tear down the wall you have covered with whitewash and will level it to the ground so that its foundation will be laid bare. When it falls, you will be destroyed in it; and you will know that I am the LORD.
26Ezk 13:15 So I will spend my wrath against the wall and against those who covered it with whitewash. I will say to you, "The wall is gone and so are those who whitewashed it,
26Ezk 13:16 those prophets of Israel who prophesied to Jerusalem and saw visions of peace for her when there was no peace, declares the Sovereign LORD." '
26Ezk 13:17 "Now, son of man, set your face against the daughters of your people who prophesy out of their own imagination. Prophesy against them
26Ezk 13:18 and say, 'This is what the Sovereign LORD says£º Woe to the women who sew magic charms on all their wrists and make veils of various lengths for their heads in order to ensnare people. Will you ensnare the lives of my people but preserve your own?
26Ezk 13:19 You have profaned me among my people for a few handfuls of barley and scraps of bread. By lying to my people, who listen to lies, you have killed those who should not have died and have spared those who should not live.
26Ezk 13:20 "'Therefore this is what the Sovereign LORD says£º I am against your magic charms with which you ensnare people like birds and I will tear them from your arms; I will set free the people that you ensnare like birds.
26Ezk 13:21 I will tear off your veils and save my people from your hands, and they will no longer fall prey to your power. Then you will know that I am the LORD.
26Ezk 13:22 Because you disheartened the righteous with your lies, when I had brought them no grief, and because you encouraged the wicked not to turn from their evil ways and so save their lives,
26Ezk 13:23 therefore you will no longer see false visions or practice divination. I will save my people from your hands. And then you will know that I am the LORD.'"
26Ezk 14:1 Some of the elders of Israel came to me and sat down in front of me.
26Ezk 14:2 Then the word of the LORD came to me£º
26Ezk 14:3 "Son of man, these men have set up idols in their hearts and put wicked stumbling blocks before their faces. Should I let them inquire of me at all?
26Ezk 14:4 Therefore speak to them and tell them, 'This is what the Sovereign LORD says£º When any Israelite sets up idols in his heart and puts a wicked stumbling block before his face and then goes to a prophet, I the LORD will answer him myself in keeping with his great idolatry.
26Ezk 14:5 I will do this to recapture the hearts of the people of Israel, who have all deserted me for their idols.'
26Ezk 14:6 "Therefore say to the house of Israel, 'This is what the Sovereign LORD says£º Repent! Turn from your idols and renounce all your detestable practices!
26Ezk 14:7 "'When any Israelite or any alien living in Israel separates himself from me and sets up idols in his heart and puts a wicked stumbling block before his face and then goes to a prophet to inquire of me, I the LORD will answer him myself.
26Ezk 14:8 I will set my face against that man and make him an example and a byword. I will cut him off from my people. Then you will know that I am the LORD.
26Ezk 14:9 "'And if the prophet is enticed to utter a prophecy, I the LORD have enticed that prophet, and I will stretch out my hand against him and destroy him from among my people Israel.
26Ezk 14:10 They will bear their guilt--the prophet will be as guilty as the one who consults him.
26Ezk 14:11 Then the people of Israel will no longer stray from me, nor will they defile themselves anymore with all their sins. They will be my people, and I will be their God, declares the Sovereign LORD.'"
26Ezk 14:12 The word of the LORD came to me£º
26Ezk 14:13 "Son of man, if a country sins against me by being unfaithful and I stretch out my hand against it to cut off its food supply and send famine upon it and kill its men and their animals,
26Ezk 14:14 even if these three men--Noah, Daniel and Job--were in it, they could save only themselves by their righteousness, declares the Sovereign LORD.
26Ezk 14:15 "Or if I send wild beasts through that country and they leave it childless and it becomes desolate so that no one can pass through it because of the beasts,
26Ezk 14:16 as surely as I live, declares the Sovereign LORD, even if these three men were in it, they could not save their own sons or daughters. They alone would be saved, but the land would be desolate.
26Ezk 14:17 "Or if I bring a sword against that country and say, 'Let the sword pass throughout the land,' and I kill its men and their animals,
26Ezk 14:18 as surely as I live, declares the Sovereign LORD, even if these three men were in it, they could not save their own sons or daughters. They alone would be saved.
26Ezk 14:19 "Or if I send a plague into that land and pour out my wrath upon it through bloodshed, killing its men and their animals,
26Ezk 14:20 as surely as I live, declares the Sovereign LORD, even if Noah, Daniel and Job were in it, they could save neither son nor daughter. They would save only themselves by their righteousness.
26Ezk 14:21 "For this is what the Sovereign LORD says£º How much worse will it be when I send against Jerusalem my four dreadful judgments--sword and famine and wild beasts and plague--to kill its men and their animals!
26Ezk 14:22 Yet there will be some survivors--sons and daughters who will be brought out of it. They will come to you, and when you see their conduct and their actions, you will be consoled regarding the disaster I have brought upon Jerusalem--every disaster I have brought upon it.
26Ezk 14:23 You will be consoled when you see their conduct and their actions, for you will know that I have done nothing in it without cause, declares the Sovereign LORD."
26Ezk 15:1 The word of the LORD came to me£º
26Ezk 15:2 "Son of man, how is the wood of a vine better than that of a branch on any of the trees in the forest?
26Ezk 15:3 Is wood ever taken from it to make anything useful? Do they make pegs from it to hang things on?
26Ezk 15:4 And after it is thrown on the fire as fuel and the fire burns both ends and chars the middle, is it then useful for anything?
26Ezk 15:5 If it was not useful for anything when it was whole, how much less can it be made into something useful when the fire has burned it and it is charred?
26Ezk 15:6 "Therefore this is what the Sovereign LORD says£º As I have given the wood of the vine among the trees of the forest as fuel for the fire, so will I treat the people living in Jerusalem.
26Ezk 15:7 I will set my face against them. Although they have come out of the fire, the fire will yet consume them. And when I set my face against them, you will know that I am the LORD.
26Ezk 15:8 I will make the land desolate because they have been unfaithful, declares the Sovereign LORD."
26Ezk 16:1 The word of the LORD came to me£º
26Ezk 16:2 "Son of man, confront Jerusalem with her detestable practices
26Ezk 16:3 and say, 'This is what the Sovereign LORD says to Jerusalem£º Your ancestry and birth were in the land of the Canaanites; your father was an Amorite and your mother a Hittite.
26Ezk 16:4 On the day you were born your cord was not cut, nor were you washed with water to make you clean, nor were you rubbed with salt or wrapped in cloths.
26Ezk 16:5 No one looked on you with pity or had compassion enough to do any of these things for you. Rather, you were thrown out into the open field, for on the day you were born you were despised.
26Ezk 16:6 "'Then I passed by and saw you kicking about in your blood, and as you lay there in your blood I said to you, "Live!"
26Ezk 16:7 I made you grow like a plant of the field. You grew up and developed and became the most beautiful of jewels. Your breasts were formed and your hair grew, you who were naked and bare.
26Ezk 16:8 "'Later I passed by, and when I looked at you and saw that you were old enough for love, I spread the corner of my garment over you and covered your nakedness. I gave you my solemn oath and entered into a covenant with you, declares the Sovereign LORD, and you became mine.
26Ezk 16:9 "'I bathed you with water and washed the blood from you and put ointments on you.
26Ezk 16:10 I clothed you with an embroidered dress and put leather sandals on you. I dressed you in fine linen and covered you with costly garments.
26Ezk 16:11 I adorned you with jewelry£º I put bracelets on your arms and a necklace around your neck,
26Ezk 16:12 and I put a ring on your nose, earrings on your ears and a beautiful crown on your head.
26Ezk 16:13 So you were adorned with gold and silver; your clothes were of fine linen and costly fabric and embroidered cloth. Your food was fine flour, honey and olive oil. You became very beautiful and rose to be a queen.
26Ezk 16:14 And your fame spread among the nations on account of your beauty, because the splendor I had given you made your beauty perfect, declares the Sovereign LORD.
26Ezk 16:15 "'But you trusted in your beauty and used your fame to become a prostitute. You lavished your favors on anyone who passed by and your beauty became his.
26Ezk 16:16 You took some of your garments to make gaudy high places, where you carried on your prostitution. Such things should not happen, nor should they ever occur.
26Ezk 16:17 You also took the fine jewelry I gave you, the jewelry made of my gold and silver, and you made for yourself male idols and engaged in prostitution with them.
26Ezk 16:18 And you took your embroidered clothes to put on them, and you offered my oil and incense before them.
26Ezk 16:19 Also the food I provided for you--the fine flour, olive oil and honey I gave you to eat--you offered as fragrant incense before them. That is what happened, declares the Sovereign LORD.
26Ezk 16:20 "'And you took your sons and daughters whom you bore to me and sacrificed them as food to the idols. Was your prostitution not enough?
26Ezk 16:21 You slaughtered my children and sacrificed them to the idols.
26Ezk 16:22 In all your detestable practices and your prostitution you did not remember the days of your youth, when you were naked and bare, kicking about in your blood.
26Ezk 16:23 "'Woe! Woe to you, declares the Sovereign LORD. In addition to all your other wickedness,
26Ezk 16:24 you built a mound for yourself and made a lofty shrine in every public square.
26Ezk 16:25 At the head of every street you built your lofty shrines and degraded your beauty, offering your body with increasing promiscuity to anyone who passed by.
26Ezk 16:26 You engaged in prostitution with the Egyptians, your lustful neighbors, and provoked me to anger with your increasing promiscuity.
26Ezk 16:27 So I stretched out my hand against you and reduced your territory; I gave you over to the greed of your enemies, the daughters of the Philistines, who were shocked by your lewd conduct.
26Ezk 16:28 You engaged in prostitution with the Assyrians too, because you were insatiable; and even after that, you still were not satisfied.
26Ezk 16:29 Then you increased your promiscuity to include Babylonia, a land of merchants, but even with this you were not satisfied.
26Ezk 16:30 "'How weak-willed you are, declares the Sovereign LORD, when you do all these things, acting like a brazen prostitute!
26Ezk 16:31 When you built your mounds at the head of every street and made your lofty shrines in every public square, you were unlike a prostitute, because you scorned payment.
26Ezk 16:32 "'You adulterous wife! You prefer strangers to your own husband!
26Ezk 16:33 Every prostitute receives a fee, but you give gifts to all your lovers, bribing them to come to you from everywhere for your illicit favors.
26Ezk 16:34 So in your prostitution you are the opposite of others; no one runs after you for your favors. You are the very opposite, for you give payment and none is given to you.
26Ezk 16:35 "'Therefore, you prostitute, hear the word of the LORD!
26Ezk 16:36 This is what the Sovereign LORD says£º Because you poured out your wealth and exposed your nakedness in your promiscuity with your lovers, and because of all your detestable idols, and because you gave them your children's blood,
26Ezk 16:37 therefore I am going to gather all your lovers, with whom you found pleasure, those you loved as well as those you hated. I will gather them against you from all around and will strip you in front of them, and they will see all your nakedness.
26Ezk 16:38 I will sentence you to the punishment of women who commit adultery and who shed blood; I will bring upon you the blood vengeance of my wrath and jealous anger.
26Ezk 16:39 Then I will hand you over to your lovers, and they will tear down your mounds and destroy your lofty shrines. They will strip you of your clothes and take your fine jewelry and leave you naked and bare.
26Ezk 16:40 They will bring a mob against you, who will stone you and hack you to pieces with their swords.
26Ezk 16:41 They will burn down your houses and inflict punishment on you in the sight of many women. I will put a stop to your prostitution, and you will no longer pay your lovers.
26Ezk 16:42 Then my wrath against you will subside and my jealous anger will turn away from you; I will be calm and no longer angry.
26Ezk 16:43 "'Because you did not remember the days of your youth but enraged me with all these things, I will surely bring down on your head what you have done, declares the Sovereign LORD. Did you not add lewdness to all your other detestable practices?
26Ezk 16:44 "'Everyone who quotes proverbs will quote this proverb about you£º "Like mother, like daughter."
26Ezk 16:45 You are a true daughter of your mother, who despised her husband and her children; and you are a true sister of your sisters, who despised their husbands and their children. Your mother was a Hittite and your father an Amorite.
26Ezk 16:46 Your older sister was Samaria, who lived to the north of you with her daughters; and your younger sister, who lived to the south of you with her daughters, was Sodom.
26Ezk 16:47 You not only walked in their ways and copied their detestable practices, but in all your ways you soon became more depraved than they.
26Ezk 16:48 As surely as I live, declares the Sovereign LORD, your sister Sodom and her daughters never did what you and your daughters have done.
26Ezk 16:49 "'Now this was the sin of your sister Sodom£º She and her daughters were arrogant, overfed and unconcerned; they did not help the poor and needy.
26Ezk 16:50 They were haughty and did detestable things before me. Therefore I did away with them as you have seen.
26Ezk 16:51 Samaria did not commit half the sins you did. You have done more detestable things than they, and have made your sisters seem righteous by all these things you have done.
26Ezk 16:52 Bear your disgrace, for you have furnished some justification for your sisters. Because your sins were more vile than theirs, they appear more righteous than you. So then, be ashamed and bear your disgrace, for you have made your sisters appear righteous.
26Ezk 16:53 "'However, I will restore the fortunes of Sodom and her daughters and of Samaria and her daughters, and your fortunes along with them,
26Ezk 16:54 so that you may bear your disgrace and be ashamed of all you have done in giving them comfort.
26Ezk 16:55 And your sisters, Sodom with her daughters and Samaria with her daughters, will return to what they were before; and you and your daughters will return to what you were before.
26Ezk 16:56 You would not even mention your sister Sodom in the day of your pride,
26Ezk 16:57 before your wickedness was uncovered. Even so, you are now scorned by the daughters of Edom and all her neighbors and the daughters of the Philistines--all those around you who despise you.
26Ezk 16:58 You will bear the consequences of your lewdness and your detestable practices, declares the LORD.
26Ezk 16:59 "'This is what the Sovereign LORD says£º I will deal with you as you deserve, because you have despised my oath by breaking the covenant.
26Ezk 16:60 Yet I will remember the covenant I made with you in the days of your youth, and I will establish an everlasting covenant with you.
26Ezk 16:61 Then you will remember your ways and be ashamed when you receive your sisters, both those who are older than you and those who are younger. I will give them to you as daughters, but not on the basis of my covenant with you.
26Ezk 16:62 So I will establish my covenant with you, and you will know that I am the LORD.
26Ezk 16:63 Then, when I make atonement for you for all you have done, you will remember and be ashamed and never again open your mouth because of your humiliation, declares the Sovereign LORD.'"
26Ezk 17:1 The word of the LORD came to me£º
26Ezk 17:2 "Son of man, set forth an allegory and tell the house of Israel a parable.
26Ezk 17:3 Say to them, 'This is what the Sovereign LORD says£º A great eagle with powerful wings, long feathers and full plumage of varied colors came to Lebanon. Taking hold of the top of a cedar,
26Ezk 17:4 he broke off its topmost shoot and carried it away to a land of merchants, where he planted it in a city of traders.
26Ezk 17:5 "'He took some of the seed of your land and put it in fertile soil. He planted it like a willow by abundant water,
26Ezk 17:6 and it sprouted and became a low, spreading vine. Its branches turned toward him, but its roots remained under it. So it became a vine and produced branches and put out leafy boughs.
26Ezk 17:7 "'But there was another great eagle with powerful wings and full plumage. The vine now sent out its roots toward him from the plot where it was planted and stretched out its branches to him for water.
26Ezk 17:8 It had been planted in good soil by abundant water so that it would produce branches, bear fruit and become a splendid vine.'
26Ezk 17:9 "Say to them, 'This is what the Sovereign LORD says£º Will it thrive? Will it not be uprooted and stripped of its fruit so that it withers? All its new growth will wither. It will not take a strong arm or many people to pull it up by the roots.
26Ezk 17:10 Even if it is transplanted, will it thrive? Will it not wither completely when the east wind strikes it--wither away in the plot where it grew?'"
26Ezk 17:11 Then the word of the LORD came to me£º
26Ezk 17:12 "Say to this rebellious house, 'Do you not know what these things mean?' Say to them£º 'The king of Babylon went to Jerusalem and carried off her king and her nobles, bringing them back with him to Babylon.
26Ezk 17:13 Then he took a member of the royal family and made a treaty with him, putting him under oath. He also carried away the leading men of the land,
26Ezk 17:14 so that the kingdom would be brought low, unable to rise again, surviving only by keeping his treaty.
26Ezk 17:15 But the king rebelled against him by sending his envoys to Egypt to get horses and a large army. Will he succeed? Will he who does such things escape? Will he break the treaty and yet escape?
26Ezk 17:16 "'As surely as I live, declares the Sovereign LORD, he shall die in Babylon, in the land of the king who put him on the throne, whose oath he despised and whose treaty he broke.
26Ezk 17:17 Pharaoh with his mighty army and great horde will be of no help to him in war, when ramps are built and siege works erected to destroy many lives.
26Ezk 17:18 He despised the oath by breaking the covenant. Because he had given his hand in pledge and yet did all these things, he shall not escape.
26Ezk 17:19 "'Therefore this is what the Sovereign LORD says£º As surely as I live, I will bring down on his head my oath that he despised and my covenant that he broke.
26Ezk 17:20 I will spread my net for him, and he will be caught in my snare. I will bring him to Babylon and execute judgment upon him there because he was unfaithful to me.
26Ezk 17:21 All his fleeing troops will fall by the sword, and the survivors will be scattered to the winds. Then you will know that I the LORD have spoken.
26Ezk 17:22 "'This is what the Sovereign LORD says£º I myself will take a shoot from the very top of a cedar and plant it; I will break off a tender sprig from its topmost shoots and plant it on a high and lofty mountain.
26Ezk 17:23 On the mountain heights of Israel I will plant it; it will produce branches and bear fruit and become a splendid cedar. Birds of every kind will nest in it; they will find shelter in the shade of its branches.
26Ezk 17:24 All the trees of the field will know that I the LORD bring down the tall tree and make the low tree grow tall. I dry up the green tree and make the dry tree flourish. "'I the LORD have spoken, and I will do it.'"
26Ezk 18:1 The word of the LORD came to me£º
26Ezk 18:2 "What do you people mean by quoting this proverb about the land of Israel£º "'The fathers eat sour grapes, and the children's teeth are set on edge'?
26Ezk 18:3 "As surely as I live, declares the Sovereign LORD, you will no longer quote this proverb in Israel.
26Ezk 18:4 For every living soul belongs to me, the father as well as the son--both alike belong to me. The soul who sins is the one who will die.
26Ezk 18:5 "Suppose there is a righteous man who does what is just and right.
26Ezk 18:6 He does not eat at the mountain shrines or look to the idols of the house of Israel. He does not defile his neighbor's wife or lie with a woman during her period.
26Ezk 18:7 He does not oppress anyone, but returns what he took in pledge for a loan. He does not commit robbery but gives his food to the hungry and provides clothing for the naked.
26Ezk 18:8 He does not lend at usury or take excessive interest. He withholds his hand from doing wrong and judges fairly between man and man.
26Ezk 18:9 He follows my decrees and faithfully keeps my laws. That man is righteous; he will surely live, declares the Sovereign LORD.
26Ezk 18:10 "Suppose he has a violent son, who sheds blood or does any of these other things
26Ezk 18:11 (though the father has done none of them)£º "He eats at the mountain shrines. He defiles his neighbor's wife.
26Ezk 18:12 He oppresses the poor and needy. He commits robbery. He does not return what he took in pledge. He looks to the idols. He does detestable things.
26Ezk 18:13 He lends at usury and takes excessive interest. Will such a man live? He will not! Because he has done all these detestable things, he will surely be put to death and his blood will be on his own head.
26Ezk 18:14 "But suppose this son has a son who sees all the sins his father commits, and though he sees them, he does not do such things£º
26Ezk 18:15 "He does not eat at the mountain shrines or look to the idols of the house of Israel. He does not defile his neighbor's wife.
26Ezk 18:16 He does not oppress anyone or require a pledge for a loan. He does not commit robbery but gives his food to the hungry and provides clothing for the naked.
26Ezk 18:17 He withholds his hand from sin and takes no usury or excessive interest. He keeps my laws and follows my decrees. He will not die for his father's sin; he will surely live.
26Ezk 18:18 But his father will die for his own sin, because he practiced extortion, robbed his brother and did what was wrong among his people.
26Ezk 18:19 "Yet you ask, 'Why does the son not share the guilt of his father?' Since the son has done what is just and right and has been careful to keep all my decrees, he will surely live.
26Ezk 18:20 The soul who sins is the one who will die. The son will not share the guilt of the father, nor will the father share the guilt of the son. The righteousness of the righteous man will be credited to him, and the wickedness of the wicked will be charged against him.
26Ezk 18:21 "But if a wicked man turns away from all the sins he has committed and keeps all my decrees and does what is just and right, he will surely live; he will not die.
26Ezk 18:22 None of the offenses he has committed will be remembered against him. Because of the righteous things he has done, he will live.
26Ezk 18:23 Do I take any pleasure in the death of the wicked? declares the Sovereign LORD. Rather, am I not pleased when they turn from their ways and live?
26Ezk 18:24 "But if a righteous man turns from his righteousness and commits sin and does the same detestable things the wicked man does, will he live? None of the righteous things he has done will be remembered. Because of the unfaithfulness he is guilty of and because of the sins he has committed, he will die.
26Ezk 18:25 "Yet you say, 'The way of the Lord is not just.' Hear, O house of Israel£º Is my way unjust? Is it not your ways that are unjust?
26Ezk 18:26 If a righteous man turns from his righteousness and commits sin, he will die for it; because of the sin he has committed he will die.
26Ezk 18:27 But if a wicked man turns away from the wickedness he has committed and does what is just and right, he will save his life.
26Ezk 18:28 Because he considers all the offenses he has committed and turns away from them, he will surely live; he will not die.
26Ezk 18:29 Yet the house of Israel says, 'The way of the Lord is not just.' Are my ways unjust, O house of Israel? Is it not your ways that are unjust?
26Ezk 18:30 "Therefore, O house of Israel, I will judge you, each one according to his ways, declares the Sovereign LORD. Repent! Turn away from all your offenses; then sin will not be your downfall.
26Ezk 18:31 Rid yourselves of all the offenses you have committed, and get a new heart and a new spirit. Why will you die, O house of Israel?
26Ezk 18:32 For I take no pleasure in the death of anyone, declares the Sovereign LORD. Repent and live!
26Ezk 19:1 "Take up a lament concerning the princes of Israel
26Ezk 19:2 and say£º "'What a lioness was your mother among the lions! She lay down among the young lions and reared her cubs.
26Ezk 19:3 She brought up one of her cubs, and he became a strong lion. He learned to tear the prey and he devoured men.
26Ezk 19:4 The nations heard about him, and he was trapped in their pit. They led him with hooks to the land of Egypt.
26Ezk 19:5 "'When she saw her hope unfulfilled, her expectation gone, she took another of her cubs and made him a strong lion.
26Ezk 19:6 He prowled among the lions, for he was now a strong lion. He learned to tear the prey and he devoured men.
26Ezk 19:7 He broke down their strongholds and devastated their towns. The land and all who were in it were terrified by his roaring.
26Ezk 19:8 Then the nations came against him, those from regions round about. They spread their net for him, and he was trapped in their pit.
26Ezk 19:9 With hooks they pulled him into a cage and brought him to the king of Babylon. They put him in prison, so his roar was heard no longer on the mountains of Israel.
26Ezk 19:10 "'Your mother was like a vine in your vineyard planted by the water; it was fruitful and full of branches because of abundant water.
26Ezk 19:11 Its branches were strong, fit for a ruler's scepter. It towered high above the thick foliage, conspicuous for its height and for its many branches.
26Ezk 19:12 But it was uprooted in fury and thrown to the ground. The east wind made it shrivel, it was stripped of its fruit; its strong branches withered and fire consumed them.
26Ezk 19:13 Now it is planted in the desert, in a dry and thirsty land.
26Ezk 19:14 Fire spread from one of its main branches and consumed its fruit. No strong branch is left on it fit for a ruler's scepter.' This is a lament and is to be used as a lament."
26Ezk 20:1 In the seventh year, in the fifth month on the tenth day, some of the elders of Israel came to inquire of the LORD, and they sat down in front of me.
26Ezk 20:2 Then the word of the LORD came to me£º
26Ezk 20:3 "Son of man, speak to the elders of Israel and say to them, 'This is what the Sovereign LORD says£º Have you come to inquire of me? As surely as I live, I will not let you inquire of me, declares the Sovereign LORD.'
26Ezk 20:4 "Will you judge them? Will you judge them, son of man? Then confront them with the detestable practices of their fathers
26Ezk 20:5 and say to them£º 'This is what the Sovereign LORD says£º On the day I chose Israel, I swore with uplifted hand to the descendants of the house of Jacob and revealed myself to them in Egypt. With uplifted hand I said to them, "I am the LORD your God."
26Ezk 20:6 On that day I swore to them that I would bring them out of Egypt into a land I had searched out for them, a land flowing with milk and honey, the most beautiful of all lands.
26Ezk 20:7 And I said to them, "Each of you, get rid of the vile images you have set your eyes on, and do not defile yourselves with the idols of Egypt. I am the LORD your God."
26Ezk 20:8 "'But they rebelled against me and would not listen to me; they did not get rid of the vile images they had set their eyes on, nor did they forsake the idols of Egypt. So I said I would pour out my wrath on them and spend my anger against them in Egypt.
26Ezk 20:9 But for the sake of my name I did what would keep it from being profaned in the eyes of the nations they lived among and in whose sight I had revealed myself to the Israelites by bringing them out of Egypt.
26Ezk 20:10 Therefore I led them out of Egypt and brought them into the desert.
26Ezk 20:11 I gave them my decrees and made known to them my laws, for the man who obeys them will live by them.
26Ezk 20:12 Also I gave them my Sabbaths as a sign between us, so they would know that I the LORD made them holy.
26Ezk 20:13 "'Yet the people of Israel rebelled against me in the desert. They did not follow my decrees but rejected my laws--although the man who obeys them will live by them--and they utterly desecrated my Sabbaths. So I said I would pour out my wrath on them and destroy them in the desert.
26Ezk 20:14 But for the sake of my name I did what would keep it from being profaned in the eyes of the nations in whose sight I had brought them out.
26Ezk 20:15 Also with uplifted hand I swore to them in the desert that I would not bring them into the land I had given them--a land flowing with milk and honey, most beautiful of all lands--
26Ezk 20:16 because they rejected my laws and did not follow my decrees and desecrated my Sabbaths. For their hearts were devoted to their idols.
26Ezk 20:17 Yet I looked on them with pity and did not destroy them or put an end to them in the desert.
26Ezk 20:18 I said to their children in the desert, "Do not follow the statutes of your fathers or keep their laws or defile yourselves with their idols.
26Ezk 20:19 I am the LORD your God; follow my decrees and be careful to keep my laws.
26Ezk 20:20 Keep my Sabbaths holy, that they may be a sign between us. Then you will know that I am the LORD your God."
26Ezk 20:21 "'But the children rebelled against me£º They did not follow my decrees, they were not careful to keep my laws--although the man who obeys them will live by them--and they desecrated my Sabbaths. So I said I would pour out my wrath on them and spend my anger against them in the desert.
26Ezk 20:22 But I withheld my hand, and for the sake of my name I did what would keep it from being profaned in the eyes of the nations in whose sight I had brought them out.
26Ezk 20:23 Also with uplifted hand I swore to them in the desert that I would disperse them among the nations and scatter them through the countries,
26Ezk 20:24 because they had not obeyed my laws but had rejected my decrees and desecrated my Sabbaths, and their eyes lusted after their fathers' idols.
26Ezk 20:25 I also gave them over to statutes that were not good and laws they could not live by;
26Ezk 20:26 I let them become defiled through their gifts--the sacrifice of every firstborn--that I might fill them with horror so they would know that I am the LORD.'
26Ezk 20:27 "Therefore, son of man, speak to the people of Israel and say to them, 'This is what the Sovereign LORD says£º In this also your fathers blasphemed me by forsaking me£º
26Ezk 20:28 When I brought them into the land I had sworn to give them and they saw any high hill or any leafy tree, there they offered their sacrifices, made offerings that provoked me to anger, presented their fragrant incense and poured out their drink offerings.
26Ezk 20:29 Then I said to them£º What is this high place you go to?'" (It is called Bamah to this day.)
26Ezk 20:30 "Therefore say to the house of Israel£º 'This is what the Sovereign LORD says£º Will you defile yourselves the way your fathers did and lust after their vile images?
26Ezk 20:31 When you offer your gifts--the sacrifice of your sons in the fire--you continue to defile yourselves with all your idols to this day. Am I to let you inquire of me, O house of Israel? As surely as I live, declares the Sovereign LORD, I will not let you inquire of me.
26Ezk 20:32 "'You say, "We want to be like the nations, like the peoples of the world, who serve wood and stone." But what you have in mind will never happen.
26Ezk 20:33 As surely as I live, declares the Sovereign LORD, I will rule over you with a mighty hand and an outstretched arm and with outpoured wrath.
26Ezk 20:34 I will bring you from the nations and gather you from the countries where you have been scattered--with a mighty hand and an outstretched arm and with outpoured wrath.
26Ezk 20:35 I will bring you into the desert of the nations and there, face to face, I will execute judgment upon you.
26Ezk 20:36 As I judged your fathers in the desert of the land of Egypt, so I will judge you, declares the Sovereign LORD.
26Ezk 20:37 I will take note of you as you pass under my rod, and I will bring you into the bond of the covenant.
26Ezk 20:38 I will purge you of those who revolt and rebel against me. Although I will bring them out of the land where they are living, yet they will not enter the land of Israel. Then you will know that I am the LORD.
26Ezk 20:39 "'As for you, O house of Israel, this is what the Sovereign LORD says£º Go and serve your idols, every one of you! But afterward you will surely listen to me and no longer profane my holy name with your gifts and idols.
26Ezk 20:40 For on my holy mountain, the high mountain of Israel, declares the Sovereign LORD, there in the land the entire house of Israel will serve me, and there I will accept them. There I will require your offerings and your choice gifts, along with all your holy sacrifices.
26Ezk 20:41 I will accept you as fragrant incense when I bring you out from the nations and gather you from the countries where you have been scattered, and I will show myself holy among you in the sight of the nations.
26Ezk 20:42 Then you will know that I am the LORD, when I bring you into the land of Israel, the land I had sworn with uplifted hand to give to your fathers.
26Ezk 20:43 There you will remember your conduct and all the actions by which you have defiled yourselves, and you will loathe yourselves for all the evil you have done.
26Ezk 20:44 You will know that I am the LORD, when I deal with you for my name's sake and not according to your evil ways and your corrupt practices, O house of Israel, declares the Sovereign LORD.'"
26Ezk 20:45 The word of the LORD came to me£º
26Ezk 20:46 "Son of man, set your face toward the south; preach against the south and prophesy against the forest of the southland.
26Ezk 20:47 Say to the southern forest£º 'Hear the word of the LORD. This is what the Sovereign LORD says£º I am about to set fire to you, and it will consume all your trees, both green and dry. The blazing flame will not be quenched, and every face from south to north will be scorched by it.
26Ezk 20:48 Everyone will see that I the LORD have kindled it; it will not be quenched.'"
26Ezk 20:49 Then I said, "Ah, Sovereign LORD! They are saying of me, 'Isn't he just telling parables?'"
26Ezk 21:1 The word of the LORD came to me£º
26Ezk 21:2 "Son of man, set your face against Jerusalem and preach against the sanctuary. Prophesy against the land of Israel
26Ezk 21:3 and say to her£º 'This is what the LORD says£º I am against you. I will draw my sword from its scabbard and cut off from you both the righteous and the wicked.
26Ezk 21:4 Because I am going to cut off the righteous and the wicked, my sword will be unsheathed against everyone from south to north.
26Ezk 21:5 Then all people will know that I the LORD have drawn my sword from its scabbard; it will not return again.'
26Ezk 21:6 "Therefore groan, son of man! Groan before them with broken heart and bitter grief.
26Ezk 21:7 And when they ask you, 'Why are you groaning?' you shall say, 'Because of the news that is coming. Every heart will melt and every hand go limp; every spirit will become faint and every knee become as weak as water.' It is coming! It will surely take place, declares the Sovereign LORD."
26Ezk 21:8 The word of the LORD came to me£º
26Ezk 21:9 "Son of man, prophesy and say, 'This is what the Lord says£º "'A sword, a sword, sharpened and polished--
26Ezk 21:10 sharpened for the slaughter, polished to flash like lightning! "'Shall we rejoice in the scepter of my son Judah? The sword despises every such stick.
26Ezk 21:11 "'The sword is appointed to be polished, to be grasped with the hand; it is sharpened and polished, made ready for the hand of the slayer.
26Ezk 21:12 Cry out and wail, son of man, for it is against my people; it is against all the princes of Israel. They are thrown to the sword along with my people. Therefore beat your breast.
26Ezk 21:13 "'Testing will surely come. And what if the scepter of Judah, which the sword despises, does not continue? declares the Sovereign LORD.'
26Ezk 21:14 "So then, son of man, prophesy and strike your hands together. Let the sword strike twice, even three times. It is a sword for slaughter--a sword for great slaughter, closing in on them from every side.
26Ezk 21:15 So that hearts may melt and the fallen be many, I have stationed the sword for slaughter at all their gates. Oh! It is made to flash like lightning, it is grasped for slaughter.
26Ezk 21:16 O sword, slash to the right, then to the left, wherever your blade is turned.
26Ezk 21:17 I too will strike my hands together, and my wrath will subside. I the LORD have spoken."
26Ezk 21:18 The word of the LORD came to me£º
26Ezk 21:19 "Son of man, mark out two roads for the sword of the king of Babylon to take, both starting from the same country. Make a signpost where the road branches off to the city.
26Ezk 21:20 Mark out one road for the sword to come against Rabbah of the Ammonites and another against Judah and fortified Jerusalem.
26Ezk 21:21 For the king of Babylon will stop at the fork in the road, at the junction of the two roads, to seek an omen£º He will cast lots with arrows, he will consult his idols, he will examine the liver.
26Ezk 21:22 Into his right hand will come the lot for Jerusalem, where he is to set up battering rams, to give the command to slaughter, to sound the battle cry, to set battering rams against the gates, to build a ramp and to erect siege works.
26Ezk 21:23 It will seem like a false omen to those who have sworn allegiance to him, but he will remind them of their guilt and take them captive.
26Ezk 21:24 "Therefore this is what the Sovereign LORD says£º 'Because you people have brought to mind your guilt by your open rebellion, revealing your sins in all that you do--because you have done this, you will be taken captive.
26Ezk 21:25 "'O profane and wicked prince of Israel, whose day has come, whose time of punishment has reached its climax,
26Ezk 21:26 this is what the Sovereign LORD says£º Take off the turban, remove the crown. It will not be as it was£º The lowly will be exalted and the exalted will be brought low.
26Ezk 21:27 A ruin! A ruin! I will make it a ruin! It will not be restored until he comes to whom it rightfully belongs; to him I will give it.'
26Ezk 21:28 "And you, son of man, prophesy and say, 'This is what the Sovereign LORD says about the Ammonites and their insults£º "'A sword, a sword, drawn for the slaughter, polished to consume and to flash like lightning!
26Ezk 21:29 Despite false visions concerning you and lying divinations about you, it will be laid on the necks of the wicked who are to be slain, whose day has come, whose time of punishment has reached its climax.
26Ezk 21:30 Return the sword to its scabbard. In the place where you were created, in the land of your ancestry, I will judge you.
26Ezk 21:31 I will pour out my wrath upon you and breathe out my fiery anger against you; I will hand you over to brutal men, men skilled in destruction.
26Ezk 21:32 You will be fuel for the fire, your blood will be shed in your land, you will be remembered no more; for I the LORD have spoken.'"
26Ezk 22:1 The word of the LORD came to me£º
26Ezk 22:2 "Son of man, will you judge her? Will you judge this city of bloodshed? Then confront her with all her detestable practices
26Ezk 22:3 and say£º 'This is what the Sovereign LORD says£º O city that brings on herself doom by shedding blood in her midst and defiles herself by making idols,
26Ezk 22:4 you have become guilty because of the blood you have shed and have become defiled by the idols you have made. You have brought your days to a close, and the end of your years has come. Therefore I will make you an object of scorn to the nations and a laughingstock to all the countries.
26Ezk 22:5 Those who are near and those who are far away will mock you, O infamous city, full of turmoil.
26Ezk 22:6 "'See how each of the princes of Israel who are in you uses his power to shed blood.
26Ezk 22:7 In you they have treated father and mother with contempt; in you they have oppressed the alien and mistreated the fatherless and the widow.
26Ezk 22:8 You have despised my holy things and desecrated my Sabbaths.
26Ezk 22:9 In you are slanderous men bent on shedding blood; in you are those who eat at the mountain shrines and commit lewd acts.
26Ezk 22:10 In you are those who dishonor their fathers' bed; in you are those who violate women during their period, when they are ceremonially unclean.
26Ezk 22:11 In you one man commits a detestable offense with his neighbor's wife, another shamefully defiles his daughter-in-law, and another violates his sister, his own father's daughter.
26Ezk 22:12 In you men accept bribes to shed blood; you take usury and excessive interest and make unjust gain from your neighbors by extortion. And you have forgotten me, declares the Sovereign LORD.
26Ezk 22:13 "'I will surely strike my hands together at the unjust gain you have made and at the blood you have shed in your midst.
26Ezk 22:14 Will your courage endure or your hands be strong in the day I deal with you? I the LORD have spoken, and I will do it.
26Ezk 22:15 I will disperse you among the nations and scatter you through the countries; and I will put an end to your uncleanness.
26Ezk 22:16 When you have been defiled in the eyes of the nations, you will know that I am the LORD.'"
26Ezk 22:17 Then the word of the LORD came to me£º
26Ezk 22:18 "Son of man, the house of Israel has become dross to me; all of them are the copper, tin, iron and lead left inside a furnace. They are but the dross of silver.
26Ezk 22:19 Therefore this is what the Sovereign LORD says£º 'Because you have all become dross, I will gather you into Jerusalem.
26Ezk 22:20 As men gather silver, copper, iron, lead and tin into a furnace to melt it with a fiery blast, so will I gather you in my anger and my wrath and put you inside the city and melt you.
26Ezk 22:21 I will gather you and I will blow on you with my fiery wrath, and you will be melted inside her.
26Ezk 22:22 As silver is melted in a furnace, so you will be melted inside her, and you will know that I the LORD have poured out my wrath upon you.'"
26Ezk 22:23 Again the word of the LORD came to me£º
26Ezk 22:24 "Son of man, say to the land, 'You are a land that has had no rain or showers in the day of wrath.'
26Ezk 22:25 There is a conspiracy of her princes within her like a roaring lion tearing its prey; they devour people, take treasures and precious things and make many widows within her.
26Ezk 22:26 Her priests do violence to my law and profane my holy things; they do not distinguish between the holy and the common; they teach that there is no difference between the unclean and the clean; and they shut their eyes to the keeping of my Sabbaths, so that I am profaned among them.
26Ezk 22:27 Her officials within her are like wolves tearing their prey; they shed blood and kill people to make unjust gain.
26Ezk 22:28 Her prophets whitewash these deeds for them by false visions and lying divinations. They say, 'This is what the Sovereign LORD says'--when the LORD has not spoken.
26Ezk 22:29 The people of the land practice extortion and commit robbery; they oppress the poor and needy and mistreat the alien, denying them justice.
26Ezk 22:30 "I looked for a man among them who would build up the wall and stand before me in the gap on behalf of the land so I would not have to destroy it, but I found none.
26Ezk 22:31 So I will pour out my wrath on them and consume them with my fiery anger, bringing down on their own heads all they have done, declares the Sovereign LORD."
26Ezk 23:1 The word of the LORD came to me£º
26Ezk 23:2 "Son of man, there were two women, daughters of the same mother.
26Ezk 23:3 They became prostitutes in Egypt, engaging in prostitution from their youth. In that land their breasts were fondled and their virgin bosoms caressed.
26Ezk 23:4 The older was named Oholah, and her sister was Oholibah. They were mine and gave birth to sons and daughters. Oholah is Samaria, and Oholibah is Jerusalem.
26Ezk 23:5 "Oholah engaged in prostitution while she was still mine; and she lusted after her lovers, the Assyrians--warriors
26Ezk 23:6 clothed in blue, governors and commanders, all of them handsome young men, and mounted horsemen.
26Ezk 23:7 She gave herself as a prostitute to all the elite of the Assyrians and defiled herself with all the idols of everyone she lusted after.
26Ezk 23:8 She did not give up the prostitution she began in Egypt, when during her youth men slept with her, caressed her virgin bosom and poured out their lust upon her.
26Ezk 23:9 "Therefore I handed her over to her lovers, the Assyrians, for whom she lusted.
26Ezk 23:10 They stripped her naked, took away her sons and daughters and killed her with the sword. She became a byword among women, and punishment was inflicted on her.
26Ezk 23:11 "Her sister Oholibah saw this, yet in her lust and prostitution she was more depraved than her sister.
26Ezk 23:12 She too lusted after the Assyrians--governors and commanders, warriors in full dress, mounted horsemen, all handsome young men.
26Ezk 23:13 I saw that she too defiled herself; both of them went the same way.
26Ezk 23:14 "But she carried her prostitution still further. She saw men portrayed on a wall, figures of Chaldeans portrayed in red,
26Ezk 23:15 with belts around their waists and flowing turbans on their heads; all of them looked like Babylonian chariot officers, natives of Chaldea.
26Ezk 23:16 As soon as she saw them, she lusted after them and sent messengers to them in Chaldea.
26Ezk 23:17 Then the Babylonians came to her, to the bed of love, and in their lust they defiled her. After she had been defiled by them, she turned away from them in disgust.
26Ezk 23:18 When she carried on her prostitution openly and exposed her nakedness, I turned away from her in disgust, just as I had turned away from her sister.
26Ezk 23:19 Yet she became more and more promiscuous as she recalled the days of her youth, when she was a prostitute in Egypt.
26Ezk 23:20 There she lusted after her lovers, whose genitals were like those of donkeys and whose emission was like that of horses.
26Ezk 23:21 So you longed for the lewdness of your youth, when in Egypt your bosom was caressed and your young breasts fondled.
26Ezk 23:22 "Therefore, Oholibah, this is what the Sovereign LORD says£º I will stir up your lovers against you, those you turned away from in disgust, and I will bring them against you from every side--
26Ezk 23:23 the Babylonians and all the Chaldeans, the men of Pekod and Shoa and Koa, and all the Assyrians with them, handsome young men, all of them governors and commanders, chariot officers and men of high rank, all mounted on horses.
26Ezk 23:24 They will come against you with weapons, chariots and wagons and with a throng of people; they will take up positions against you on every side with large and small shields and with helmets. I will turn you over to them for punishment, and they will punish you according to their standards.
26Ezk 23:25 I will direct my jealous anger against you, and they will deal with you in fury. They will cut off your noses and your ears, and those of you who are left will fall by the sword. They will take away your sons and daughters, and those of you who are left will be consumed by fire.
26Ezk 23:26 They will also strip you of your clothes and take your fine jewelry.
26Ezk 23:27 So I will put a stop to the lewdness and prostitution you began in Egypt. You will not look on these things with longing or remember Egypt anymore.
26Ezk 23:28 "For this is what the Sovereign LORD says£º I am about to hand you over to those you hate, to those you turned away from in disgust.
26Ezk 23:29 They will deal with you in hatred and take away everything you have worked for. They will leave you naked and bare, and the shame of your prostitution will be exposed. Your lewdness and promiscuity
26Ezk 23:30 have brought this upon you, because you lusted after the nations and defiled yourself with their idols.
26Ezk 23:31 You have gone the way of your sister; so I will put her cup into your hand.
26Ezk 23:32 "This is what the Sovereign LORD says£º "You will drink your sister's cup, a cup large and deep; it will bring scorn and derision, for it holds so much.
26Ezk 23:33 You will be filled with drunkenness and sorrow, the cup of ruin and desolation, the cup of your sister Samaria.
26Ezk 23:34 You will drink it and drain it dry; you will dash it to pieces and tear your breasts. I have spoken, declares the Sovereign LORD.
26Ezk 23:35 "Therefore this is what the Sovereign LORD says£º Since you have forgotten me and thrust me behind your back, you must bear the consequences of your lewdness and prostitution."
26Ezk 23:36 The LORD said to me£º "Son of man, will you judge Oholah and Oholibah? Then confront them with their detestable practices,
26Ezk 23:37 for they have committed adultery and blood is on their hands. They committed adultery with their idols; they even sacrificed their children, whom they bore to me, as food for them.
26Ezk 23:38 They have also done this to me£º At that same time they defiled my sanctuary and desecrated my Sabbaths.
26Ezk 23:39 On the very day they sacrificed their children to their idols, they entered my sanctuary and desecrated it. That is what they did in my house.
26Ezk 23:40 "They even sent messengers for men who came from far away, and when they arrived you bathed yourself for them, painted your eyes and put on your jewelry.
26Ezk 23:41 You sat on an elegant couch, with a table spread before it on which you had placed the incense and oil that belonged to me.
26Ezk 23:42 "The noise of a carefree crowd was around her; Sabeans were brought from the desert along with men from the rabble, and they put bracelets on the arms of the woman and her sister and beautiful crowns on their heads.
26Ezk 23:43 Then I said about the one worn out by adultery, 'Now let them use her as a prostitute, for that is all she is.'
26Ezk 23:44 And they slept with her. As men sleep with a prostitute, so they slept with those lewd women, Oholah and Oholibah.
26Ezk 23:45 But righteous men will sentence them to the punishment of women who commit adultery and shed blood, because they are adulterous and blood is on their hands.
26Ezk 23:46 "This is what the Sovereign LORD says£º Bring a mob against them and give them over to terror and plunder.
26Ezk 23:47 The mob will stone them and cut them down with their swords; they will kill their sons and daughters and burn down their houses.
26Ezk 23:48 "So I will put an end to lewdness in the land, that all women may take warning and not imitate you.
26Ezk 23:49 You will suffer the penalty for your lewdness and bear the consequences of your sins of idolatry. Then you will know that I am the Sovereign LORD."
26Ezk 24:1 In the ninth year, in the tenth month on the tenth day, the word of the LORD came to me£º
26Ezk 24:2 "Son of man, record this date, this very date, because the king of Babylon has laid siege to Jerusalem this very day.
26Ezk 24:3 Tell this rebellious house a parable and say to them£º 'This is what the Sovereign LORD says£º "'Put on the cooking pot; put it on and pour water into it.
26Ezk 24:4 Put into it the pieces of meat, all the choice pieces--the leg and the shoulder. Fill it with the best of these bones;
26Ezk 24:5 take the pick of the flock. Pile wood beneath it for the bones; bring it to a boil and cook the bones in it.
26Ezk 24:6 "'For this is what the Sovereign LORD says£º "'Woe to the city of bloodshed, to the pot now encrusted, whose deposit will not go away! Empty it piece by piece without casting lots for them.
26Ezk 24:7 "'For the blood she shed is in her midst£º She poured it on the bare rock; she did not pour it on the ground, where the dust would cover it.
26Ezk 24:8 To stir up wrath and take revenge I put her blood on the bare rock, so that it would not be covered.
26Ezk 24:9 "'Therefore this is what the Sovereign LORD says£º "'Woe to the city of bloodshed! I, too, will pile the wood high.
26Ezk 24:10 So heap on the wood and kindle the fire. Cook the meat well, mixing in the spices; and let the bones be charred.
26Ezk 24:11 Then set the empty pot on the coals till it becomes hot and its copper glows so its impurities may be melted and its deposit burned away.
26Ezk 24:12 It has frustrated all efforts; its heavy deposit has not been removed, not even by fire.
26Ezk 24:13 "'Now your impurity is lewdness. Because I tried to cleanse you but you would not be cleansed from your impurity, you will not be clean again until my wrath against you has subsided.
26Ezk 24:14 "'I the LORD have spoken. The time has come for me to act. I will not hold back; I will not have pity, nor will I relent. You will be judged according to your conduct and your actions, declares the Sovereign LORD.'"
26Ezk 24:15 The word of the LORD came to me£º
26Ezk 24:16 "Son of man, with one blow I am about to take away from you the delight of your eyes. Yet do not lament or weep or shed any tears.
26Ezk 24:17 Groan quietly; do not mourn for the dead. Keep your turban fastened and your sandals on your feet; do not cover the lower part of your face or eat the customary food of mourners."
26Ezk 24:18 So I spoke to the people in the morning, and in the evening my wife died. The next morning I did as I had been commanded.
26Ezk 24:19 Then the people asked me, "Won't you tell us what these things have to do with us?"
26Ezk 24:20 So I said to them, "The word of the LORD came to me£º
26Ezk 24:21 Say to the house of Israel, 'This is what the Sovereign LORD says£º I am about to desecrate my sanctuary--the stronghold in which you take pride, the delight of your eyes, the object of your affection. The sons and daughters you left behind will fall by the sword.
26Ezk 24:22 And you will do as I have done. You will not cover the lower part of your face or eat the customary food of mourners.
26Ezk 24:23 You will keep your turbans on your heads and your sandals on your feet. You will not mourn or weep but will waste away because of your sins and groan among yourselves.
26Ezk 24:24 Ezekiel will be a sign to you; you will do just as he has done. When this happens, you will know that I am the Sovereign LORD.'
26Ezk 24:25 "And you, son of man, on the day I take away their stronghold, their joy and glory, the delight of their eyes, their heart's desire, and their sons and daughters as well--
26Ezk 24:26 on that day a fugitive will come to tell you the news.
26Ezk 24:27 At that time your mouth will be opened; you will speak with him and will no longer be silent. So you will be a sign to them, and they will know that I am the LORD."
26Ezk 25:1 The word of the LORD came to me£º
26Ezk 25:2 "Son of man, set your face against the Ammonites and prophesy against them.
26Ezk 25:3 Say to them, 'Hear the word of the Sovereign LORD. This is what the Sovereign LORD says£º Because you said "Aha!" over my sanctuary when it was desecrated and over the land of Israel when it was laid waste and over the people of Judah when they went into exile,
26Ezk 25:4 therefore I am going to give you to the people of the East as a possession. They will set up their camps and pitch their tents among you; they will eat your fruit and drink your milk.
26Ezk 25:5 I will turn Rabbah into a pasture for camels and Ammon into a resting place for sheep. Then you will know that I am the LORD.
26Ezk 25:6 For this is what the Sovereign LORD says£º Because you have clapped your hands and stamped your feet, rejoicing with all the malice of your heart against the land of Israel,
26Ezk 25:7 therefore I will stretch out my hand against you and give you as plunder to the nations. I will cut you off from the nations and exterminate you from the countries. I will destroy you, and you will know that I am the LORD.'"
26Ezk 25:8 "This is what the Sovereign LORD says£º 'Because Moab and Seir said, "Look, the house of Judah has become like all the other nations,"
26Ezk 25:9 therefore I will expose the flank of Moab, beginning at its frontier towns--Beth Jeshimoth, Baal Meon and Kiriathaim--the glory of that land.
26Ezk 25:10 I will give Moab along with the Ammonites to the people of the East as a possession, so that the Ammonites will not be remembered among the nations;
26Ezk 25:11 and I will inflict punishment on Moab. Then they will know that I am the LORD.'"
26Ezk 25:12 "This is what the Sovereign LORD says£º 'Because Edom took revenge on the house of Judah and became very guilty by doing so,
26Ezk 25:13 therefore this is what the Sovereign LORD says£º I will stretch out my hand against Edom and kill its men and their animals. I will lay it waste, and from Teman to Dedan they will fall by the sword.
26Ezk 25:14 I will take vengeance on Edom by the hand of my people Israel, and they will deal with Edom in accordance with my anger and my wrath; they will know my vengeance, declares the Sovereign LORD.'"
26Ezk 25:15 "This is what the Sovereign LORD says£º 'Because the Philistines acted in vengeance and took revenge with malice in their hearts, and with ancient hostility sought to destroy Judah,
26Ezk 25:16 therefore this is what the Sovereign LORD says£º I am about to stretch out my hand against the Philistines, and I will cut off the Kerethites and destroy those remaining along the coast.
26Ezk 25:17 I will carry out great vengeance on them and punish them in my wrath. Then they will know that I am the LORD, when I take vengeance on them.'"
26Ezk 26:1 In the eleventh year, on the first day of the month, the word of the LORD came to me£º
26Ezk 26:2 "Son of man, because Tyre has said of Jerusalem, 'Aha! The gate to the nations is broken, and its doors have swung open to me; now that she lies in ruins I will prosper,'
26Ezk 26:3 therefore this is what the Sovereign LORD says£º I am against you, O Tyre, and I will bring many nations against you, like the sea casting up its waves.
26Ezk 26:4 They will destroy the walls of Tyre and pull down her towers; I will scrape away her rubble and make her a bare rock.
26Ezk 26:5 Out in the sea she will become a place to spread fishnets, for I have spoken, declares the Sovereign LORD. She will become plunder for the nations,
26Ezk 26:6 and her settlements on the mainland will be ravaged by the sword. Then they will know that I am the LORD.
26Ezk 26:7 "For this is what the Sovereign LORD says£º From the north I am going to bring against Tyre Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon, king of kings, with horses and chariots, with horsemen and a great army.
26Ezk 26:8 He will ravage your settlements on the mainland with the sword; he will set up siege works against you, build a ramp up to your walls and raise his shields against you.
26Ezk 26:9 He will direct the blows of his battering rams against your walls and demolish your towers with his weapons.
26Ezk 26:10 His horses will be so many that they will cover you with dust. Your walls will tremble at the noise of the war horses, wagons and chariots when he enters your gates as men enter a city whose walls have been broken through.
26Ezk 26:11 The hoofs of his horses will trample all your streets; he will kill your people with the sword, and your strong pillars will fall to the ground.
26Ezk 26:12 They will plunder your wealth and loot your merchandise; they will break down your walls and demolish your fine houses and throw your stones, timber and rubble into the sea.
26Ezk 26:13 I will put an end to your noisy songs, and the music of your harps will be heard no more.
26Ezk 26:14 I will make you a bare rock, and you will become a place to spread fishnets. You will never be rebuilt, for I the LORD have spoken, declares the Sovereign LORD.
26Ezk 26:15 "This is what the Sovereign LORD says to Tyre£º Will not the coastlands tremble at the sound of your fall, when the wounded groan and the slaughter takes place in you?
26Ezk 26:16 Then all the princes of the coast will step down from their thrones and lay aside their robes and take off their embroidered garments. Clothed with terror, they will sit on the ground, trembling every moment, appalled at you.
26Ezk 26:17 Then they will take up a lament concerning you and say to you£º "'How you are destroyed, O city of renown, peopled by men of the sea! You were a power on the seas, you and your citizens; you put your terror on all who lived there.
26Ezk 26:18 Now the coastlands tremble on the day of your fall; the islands in the sea are terrified at your collapse.'
26Ezk 26:19 "This is what the Sovereign LORD says£º When I make you a desolate city, like cities no longer inhabited, and when I bring the ocean depths over you and its vast waters cover you,
26Ezk 26:20 then I will bring you down with those who go down to the pit, to the people of long ago. I will make you dwell in the earth below, as in ancient ruins, with those who go down to the pit, and you will not return or take your place in the land of the living.
26Ezk 26:21 I will bring you to a horrible end and you will be no more. You will be sought, but you will never again be found, declares the Sovereign LORD."
26Ezk 27:1 The word of the LORD came to me£º
26Ezk 27:2 "Son of man, take up a lament concerning Tyre.
26Ezk 27:3 Say to Tyre, situated at the gateway to the sea, merchant of peoples on many coasts, 'This is what the Sovereign LORD says£º "'You say, O Tyre, "I am perfect in beauty."
26Ezk 27:4 Your domain was on the high seas; your builders brought your beauty to perfection.
26Ezk 27:5 They made all your timbers of pine trees from Senir; they took a cedar from Lebanon to make a mast for you.
26Ezk 27:6 Of oaks from Bashan they made your oars; of cypress wood from the coasts of Cyprus they made your deck, inlaid with ivory.
26Ezk 27:7 Fine embroidered linen from Egypt was your sail and served as your banner; your awnings were of blue and purple from the coasts of Elishah.
26Ezk 27:8 Men of Sidon and Arvad were your oarsmen; your skilled men, O Tyre, were aboard as your seamen.
26Ezk 27:9 Veteran craftsmen of Gebal were on board as shipwrights to caulk your seams. All the ships of the sea and their sailors came alongside to trade for your wares.
26Ezk 27:10 "'Men of Persia, Lydia and Put served as soldiers in your army. They hung their shields and helmets on your walls, bringing you splendor.
26Ezk 27:11 Men of Arvad and Helech manned your walls on every side; men of Gammad were in your towers. They hung their shields around your walls; they brought your beauty to perfection.
26Ezk 27:12 "'Tarshish did business with you because of your great wealth of goods; they exchanged silver, iron, tin and lead for your merchandise.
26Ezk 27:13 "'Greece, Tubal and Meshech traded with you; they exchanged slaves and articles of bronze for your wares.
26Ezk 27:14 "'Men of Beth Togarmah exchanged work horses, war horses and mules for your merchandise.
26Ezk 27:15 "'The men of Rhodes traded with you, and many coastlands were your customers; they paid you with ivory tusks and ebony.
26Ezk 27:16 "'Aram did business with you because of your many products; they exchanged turquoise, purple fabric, embroidered work, fine linen, coral and rubies for your merchandise.
26Ezk 27:17 "'Judah and Israel traded with you; they exchanged wheat from Minnith and confections, honey, oil and balm for your wares.
26Ezk 27:18 "'Damascus, because of your many products and great wealth of goods, did business with you in wine from Helbon and wool from Zahar.
26Ezk 27:19 "'Danites and Greeks from Uzal bought your merchandise; they exchanged wrought iron, cassia and calamus for your wares.
26Ezk 27:20 "'Dedan traded in saddle blankets with you.
26Ezk 27:21 "'Arabia and all the princes of Kedar were your customers; they did business with you in lambs, rams and goats.
26Ezk 27:22 "'The merchants of Sheba and Raamah traded with you; for your merchandise they exchanged the finest of all kinds of spices and precious stones, and gold.
26Ezk 27:23 "'Haran, Canneh and Eden and merchants of Sheba, Asshur and Kilmad traded with you.
26Ezk 27:24 In your marketplace they traded with you beautiful garments, blue fabric, embroidered work and multicolored rugs with cords twisted and tightly knotted.
26Ezk 27:25 "'The ships of Tarshish serve as carriers for your wares. You are filled with heavy cargo in the heart of the sea.
26Ezk 27:26 Your oarsmen take you out to the high seas. But the east wind will break you to pieces in the heart of the sea.
26Ezk 27:27 Your wealth, merchandise and wares, your mariners, seamen and shipwrights, your merchants and all your soldiers, and everyone else on board will sink into the heart of the sea on the day of your shipwreck.
26Ezk 27:28 The shorelands will quake when your seamen cry out.
26Ezk 27:29 All who handle the oars will abandon their ships; the mariners and all the seamen will stand on the shore.
26Ezk 27:30 They will raise their voice and cry bitterly over you; they will sprinkle dust on their heads and roll in ashes.
26Ezk 27:31 They will shave their heads because of you and will put on sackcloth. They will weep over you with anguish of soul and with bitter mourning.
26Ezk 27:32 As they wail and mourn over you, they will take up a lament concerning you£º "Who was ever silenced like Tyre, surrounded by the sea?"
26Ezk 27:33 When your merchandise went out on the seas, you satisfied many nations; with your great wealth and your wares you enriched the kings of the earth.
26Ezk 27:34 Now you are shattered by the sea in the depths of the waters; your wares and all your company have gone down with you.
26Ezk 27:35 All who live in the coastlands are appalled at you; their kings shudder with horror and their faces are distorted with fear.
26Ezk 27:36 The merchants among the nations hiss at you; you have come to a horrible end and will be no more.'"
26Ezk 28:1 The word of the LORD came to me£º
26Ezk 28:2 "Son of man, say to the ruler of Tyre, 'This is what the Sovereign LORD says£º "'In the pride of your heart you say, "I am a god; I sit on the throne of a god in the heart of the seas." But you are a man and not a god, though you think you are as wise as a god.
26Ezk 28:3 Are you wiser than Daniel? Is no secret hidden from you?
26Ezk 28:4 By your wisdom and understanding you have gained wealth for yourself and amassed gold and silver in your treasuries.
26Ezk 28:5 By your great skill in trading you have increased your wealth, and because of your wealth your heart has grown proud.
26Ezk 28:6 "'Therefore this is what the Sovereign LORD says£º "'Because you think you are wise, as wise as a god,
26Ezk 28:7 I am going to bring foreigners against you, the most ruthless of nations; they will draw their swords against your beauty and wisdom and pierce your shining splendor.
26Ezk 28:8 They will bring you down to the pit, and you will die a violent death in the heart of the seas.
26Ezk 28:9 Will you then say, "I am a god," in the presence of those who kill you? You will be but a man, not a god, in the hands of those who slay you.
26Ezk 28:10 You will die the death of the uncircumcised at the hands of foreigners. I have spoken, declares the Sovereign LORD.'"
26Ezk 28:11 The word of the LORD came to me£º
26Ezk 28:12 "Son of man, take up a lament concerning the king of Tyre and say to him£º 'This is what the Sovereign LORD says£º "'You were the model of perfection, full of wisdom and perfect in beauty.
26Ezk 28:13 You were in Eden, the garden of God; every precious stone adorned you£º ruby, topaz and emerald, chrysolite, onyx and jasper, sapphire, turquoise and beryl. Your settings and mountings were made of gold; on the day you were created they were prepared.
26Ezk 28:14 You were anointed as a guardian cherub, for so I ordained you. You were on the holy mount of God; you walked among the fiery stones.
26Ezk 28:15 You were blameless in your ways from the day you were created till wickedness was found in you.
26Ezk 28:16 Through your widespread trade you were filled with violence, and you sinned. So I drove you in disgrace from the mount of God, and I expelled you, O guardian cherub, from among the fiery stones.
26Ezk 28:17 Your heart became proud on account of your beauty, and you corrupted your wisdom because of your splendor. So I threw you to the earth; I made a spectacle of you before kings.
26Ezk 28:18 By your many sins and dishonest trade you have desecrated your sanctuaries. So I made a fire come out from you, and it consumed you, and I reduced you to ashes on the ground in the sight of all who were watching.
26Ezk 28:19 All the nations who knew you are appalled at you; you have come to a horrible end and will be no more.'"
26Ezk 28:20 The word of the LORD came to me£º
26Ezk 28:21 "Son of man, set your face against Sidon; prophesy against her
26Ezk 28:22 and say£º 'This is what the Sovereign LORD says£º "'I am against you, O Sidon, and I will gain glory within you. They will know that I am the LORD, when I inflict punishment on her and show myself holy within her.
26Ezk 28:23 I will send a plague upon her and make blood flow in her streets. The slain will fall within her, with the sword against her on every side. Then they will know that I am the LORD.
26Ezk 28:24 "'No longer will the people of Israel have malicious neighbors who are painful briers and sharp thorns. Then they will know that I am the Sovereign LORD.
26Ezk 28:25 "'This is what the Sovereign LORD says£º When I gather the people of Israel from the nations where they have been scattered, I will show myself holy among them in the sight of the nations. Then they will live in their own land, which I gave to my servant Jacob.
26Ezk 28:26 They will live there in safety and will build houses and plant vineyards; they will live in safety when I inflict punishment on all their neighbors who maligned them. Then they will know that I am the LORD their God.'"
26Ezk 29:1 In the tenth year, in the tenth month on the twelfth day, the word of the LORD came to me£º
26Ezk 29:2 "Son of man, set your face against Pharaoh king of Egypt and prophesy against him and against all Egypt.
26Ezk 29:3 Speak to him and say£º 'This is what the Sovereign LORD says£º "'I am against you, Pharaoh king of Egypt, you great monster lying among your streams. You say, "The Nile is mine; I made it for myself."
26Ezk 29:4 But I will put hooks in your jaws and make the fish of your streams stick to your scales. I will pull you out from among your streams, with all the fish sticking to your scales.
26Ezk 29:5 I will leave you in the desert, you and all the fish of your streams. You will fall on the open field and not be gathered or picked up. I will give you as food to the beasts of the earth and the birds of the air.
26Ezk 29:6 Then all who live in Egypt will know that I am the LORD. "'You have been a staff of reed for the house of Israel.
26Ezk 29:7 When they grasped you with their hands, you splintered and you tore open their shoulders; when they leaned on you, you broke and their backs were wrenched.
26Ezk 29:8 "'Therefore this is what the Sovereign LORD says£º I will bring a sword against you and kill your men and their animals.
26Ezk 29:9 Egypt will become a desolate wasteland. Then they will know that I am the LORD. "'Because you said, "The Nile is mine; I made it,"
26Ezk 29:10 therefore I am against you and against your streams, and I will make the land of Egypt a ruin and a desolate waste from Migdol to Aswan, as far as the border of Cush.
26Ezk 29:11 No foot of man or animal will pass through it; no one will live there for forty years.
26Ezk 29:12 I will make the land of Egypt desolate among devastated lands, and her cities will lie desolate forty years among ruined cities. And I will disperse the Egyptians among the nations and scatter them through the countries.
26Ezk 29:13 "'Yet this is what the Sovereign LORD says£º At the end of forty years I will gather the Egyptians from the nations where they were scattered.
26Ezk 29:14 I will bring them back from captivity and return them to Upper Egypt, the land of their ancestry. There they will be a lowly kingdom.
26Ezk 29:15 It will be the lowliest of kingdoms and will never again exalt itself above the other nations. I will make it so weak that it will never again rule over the nations.
26Ezk 29:16 Egypt will no longer be a source of confidence for the people of Israel but will be a reminder of their sin in turning to her for help. Then they will know that I am the Sovereign LORD.'"
26Ezk 29:17 In the twenty-seventh year, in the first month on the first day, the word of the LORD came to me£º
26Ezk 29:18 "Son of man, Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon drove his army in a hard campaign against Tyre; every head was rubbed bare and every shoulder made raw. Yet he and his army got no reward from the campaign he led against Tyre.
26Ezk 29:19 Therefore this is what the Sovereign LORD says£º I am going to give Egypt to Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon, and he will carry off its wealth. He will loot and plunder the land as pay for his army.
26Ezk 29:20 I have given him Egypt as a reward for his efforts because he and his army did it for me, declares the Sovereign LORD.
26Ezk 29:21 "On that day I will make a horn grow for the house of Israel, and I will open your mouth among them. Then they will know that I am the LORD."
26Ezk 30:1 The word of the LORD came to me£º
26Ezk 30:2 "Son of man, prophesy and say£º 'This is what the Sovereign LORD says£º "'Wail and say, "Alas for that day!"
26Ezk 30:3 For the day is near, the day of the LORD is near--a day of clouds, a time of doom for the nations.
26Ezk 30:4 A sword will come against Egypt, and anguish will come upon Cush. When the slain fall in Egypt, her wealth will be carried away and her foundations torn down.
26Ezk 30:5 Cush and Put, Lydia and all Arabia, Libya and the people of the covenant land will fall by the sword along with Egypt.
26Ezk 30:6 "'This is what the LORD says£º "'The allies of Egypt will fall and her proud strength will fail. From Migdol to Aswan they will fall by the sword within her, declares the Sovereign LORD.
26Ezk 30:7 "'They will be desolate among desolate lands, and their cities will lie among ruined cities.
26Ezk 30:8 Then they will know that I am the LORD, when I set fire to Egypt and all her helpers are crushed.
26Ezk 30:9 "'On that day messengers will go out from me in ships to frighten Cush out of her complacency. Anguish will take hold of them on the day of Egypt's doom, for it is sure to come.
26Ezk 30:10 "'This is what the Sovereign LORD says£º "'I will put an end to the hordes of Egypt by the hand of Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon.
26Ezk 30:11 He and his army--the most ruthless of nations--will be brought in to destroy the land. They will draw their swords against Egypt and fill the land with the slain.
26Ezk 30:12 I will dry up the streams of the Nile and sell the land to evil men; by the hand of foreigners I will lay waste the land and everything in it. I the LORD have spoken.
26Ezk 30:13 "'This is what the Sovereign LORD says£º "'I will destroy the idols and put an end to the images in Memphis. No longer will there be a prince in Egypt, and I will spread fear throughout the land.
26Ezk 30:14 I will lay waste Upper Egypt, set fire to Zoan and inflict punishment on Thebes.
26Ezk 30:15 I will pour out my wrath on Pelusium, the stronghold of Egypt, and cut off the hordes of Thebes.
26Ezk 30:16 I will set fire to Egypt; Pelusium will writhe in agony. Thebes will be taken by storm; Memphis will be in constant distress.
26Ezk 30:17 The young men of Heliopolis and Bubastis will fall by the sword, and the cities themselves will go into captivity.
26Ezk 30:18 Dark will be the day at Tahpanhes when I break the yoke of Egypt; there her proud strength will come to an end. She will be covered with clouds, and her villages will go into captivity.
26Ezk 30:19 So I will inflict punishment on Egypt, and they will know that I am the LORD.'"
26Ezk 30:20 In the eleventh year, in the first month on the seventh day, the word of the LORD came to me£º
26Ezk 30:21 "Son of man, I have broken the arm of Pharaoh king of Egypt. It has not been bound up for healing or put in a splint so as to become strong enough to hold a sword.
26Ezk 30:22 Therefore this is what the Sovereign LORD says£º I am against Pharaoh king of Egypt. I will break both his arms, the good arm as well as the broken one, and make the sword fall from his hand.
26Ezk 30:23 I will disperse the Egyptians among the nations and scatter them through the countries.
26Ezk 30:24 I will strengthen the arms of the king of Babylon and put my sword in his hand, but I will break the arms of Pharaoh, and he will groan before him like a mortally wounded man.
26Ezk 30:25 I will strengthen the arms of the king of Babylon, but the arms of Pharaoh will fall limp. Then they will know that I am the LORD, when I put my sword into the hand of the king of Babylon and he brandishes it against Egypt.
26Ezk 30:26 I will disperse the Egyptians among the nations and scatter them through the countries. Then they will know that I am the LORD."
26Ezk 31:1 In the eleventh year, in the third month on the first day, the word of the LORD came to me£º
26Ezk 31:2 "Son of man, say to Pharaoh king of Egypt and to his hordes£º "'Who can be compared with you in majesty?
26Ezk 31:3 Consider Assyria, once a cedar in Lebanon, with beautiful branches overshadowing the forest; it towered on high, its top above the thick foliage.
26Ezk 31:4 The waters nourished it, deep springs made it grow tall; their streams flowed all around its base and sent their channels to all the trees of the field.
26Ezk 31:5 So it towered higher than all the trees of the field; its boughs increased and its branches grew long, spreading because of abundant waters.
26Ezk 31:6 All the birds of the air nested in its boughs, all the beasts of the field gave birth under its branches; all the great nations lived in its shade.
26Ezk 31:7 It was majestic in beauty, with its spreading boughs, for its roots went down to abundant waters.
26Ezk 31:8 The cedars in the garden of God could not rival it, nor could the pine trees equal its boughs, nor could the plane trees compare with its branches--no tree in the garden of God could match its beauty.
26Ezk 31:9 I made it beautiful with abundant branches, the envy of all the trees of Eden in the garden of God.
26Ezk 31:10 "'Therefore this is what the Sovereign LORD says£º Because it towered on high, lifting its top above the thick foliage, and because it was proud of its height,
26Ezk 31:11 I handed it over to the ruler of the nations, for him to deal with according to its wickedness. I cast it aside,
26Ezk 31:12 and the most ruthless of foreign nations cut it down and left it. Its boughs fell on the mountains and in all the valleys; its branches lay broken in all the ravines of the land. All the nations of the earth came out from under its shade and left it.
26Ezk 31:13 All the birds of the air settled on the fallen tree, and all the beasts of the field were among its branches.
26Ezk 31:14 Therefore no other trees by the waters are ever to tower proudly on high, lifting their tops above the thick foliage. No other trees so well-watered are ever to reach such a height; they are all destined for death, for the earth below, among mortal men, with those who go down to the pit.
26Ezk 31:15 "'This is what the Sovereign LORD says£º On the day it was brought down to the grave I covered the deep springs with mourning for it; I held back its streams, and its abundant waters were restrained. Because of it I clothed Lebanon with gloom, and all the trees of the field withered away.
26Ezk 31:16 I made the nations tremble at the sound of its fall when I brought it down to the grave with those who go down to the pit. Then all the trees of Eden, the choicest and best of Lebanon, all the trees that were well-watered, were consoled in the earth below.
26Ezk 31:17 Those who lived in its shade, its allies among the nations, had also gone down to the grave with it, joining those killed by the sword.
26Ezk 31:18 "'Which of the trees of Eden can be compared with you in splendor and majesty? Yet you, too, will be brought down with the trees of Eden to the earth below; you will lie among the uncircumcised, with those killed by the sword. "'This is Pharaoh and all his hordes, declares the Sovereign LORD.'"
26Ezk 32:1 In the twelfth year, in the twelfth month on the first day, the word of the LORD came to me£º
26Ezk 32:2 "Son of man, take up a lament concerning Pharaoh king of Egypt and say to him£º "'You are like a lion among the nations; you are like a monster in the seas thrashing about in your streams, churning the water with your feet and muddying the streams.
26Ezk 32:3 "'This is what the Sovereign LORD says£º "'With a great throng of people I will cast my net over you, and they will haul you up in my net.
26Ezk 32:4 I will throw you on the land and hurl you on the open field. I will let all the birds of the air settle on you and all the beasts of the earth gorge themselves on you.
26Ezk 32:5 I will spread your flesh on the mountains and fill the valleys with your remains.
26Ezk 32:6 I will drench the land with your flowing blood all the way to the mountains, and the ravines will be filled with your flesh.
26Ezk 32:7 When I snuff you out, I will cover the heavens and darken their stars; I will cover the sun with a cloud, and the moon will not give its light.
26Ezk 32:8 All the shining lights in the heavens I will darken over you; I will bring darkness over your land, declares the Sovereign LORD.
26Ezk 32:9 I will trouble the hearts of many peoples when I bring about your destruction among the nations, among lands you have not known.
26Ezk 32:10 I will cause many peoples to be appalled at you, and their kings will shudder with horror because of you when I brandish my sword before them. On the day of your downfall each of them will tremble every moment for his life.
26Ezk 32:11 "'For this is what the Sovereign LORD says£º "'The sword of the king of Babylon will come against you.
26Ezk 32:12 I will cause your hordes to fall by the swords of mighty men--the most ruthless of all nations. They will shatter the pride of Egypt, and all her hordes will be overthrown.
26Ezk 32:13 I will destroy all her cattle from beside abundant waters no longer to be stirred by the foot of man or muddied by the hoofs of cattle.
26Ezk 32:14 Then I will let her waters settle and make her streams flow like oil, declares the Sovereign LORD.
26Ezk 32:15 When I make Egypt desolate and strip the land of everything in it, when I strike down all who live there, then they will know that I am the LORD.'
26Ezk 32:16 "This is the lament they will chant for her. The daughters of the nations will chant it; for Egypt and all her hordes they will chant it, declares the Sovereign LORD."
26Ezk 32:17 In the twelfth year, on the fifteenth day of the month, the word of the LORD came to me£º
26Ezk 32:18 "Son of man, wail for the hordes of Egypt and consign to the earth below both her and the daughters of mighty nations, with those who go down to the pit.
26Ezk 32:19 Say to them, 'Are you more favored than others? Go down and be laid among the uncircumcised.'
26Ezk 32:20 They will fall among those killed by the sword. The sword is drawn; let her be dragged off with all her hordes.
26Ezk 32:21 From within the grave the mighty leaders will say of Egypt and her allies, 'They have come down and they lie with the uncircumcised, with those killed by the sword.'
26Ezk 32:22 "Assyria is there with her whole army; she is surrounded by the graves of all her slain, all who have fallen by the sword.
26Ezk 32:23 Their graves are in the depths of the pit and her army lies around her grave. All who had spread terror in the land of the living are slain, fallen by the sword.
26Ezk 32:24 "Elam is there, with all her hordes around her grave. All of them are slain, fallen by the sword. All who had spread terror in the land of the living went down uncircumcised to the earth below. They bear their shame with those who go down to the pit.
26Ezk 32:25 A bed is made for her among the slain, with all her hordes around her grave. All of them are uncircumcised, killed by the sword. Because their terror had spread in the land of the living, they bear their shame with those who go down to the pit; they are laid among the slain.
26Ezk 32:26 "Meshech and Tubal are there, with all their hordes around their graves. All of them are uncircumcised, killed by the sword because they spread their terror in the land of the living.
26Ezk 32:27 Do they not lie with the other uncircumcised warriors who have fallen, who went down to the grave with their weapons of war, whose swords were placed under their heads? The punishment for their sins rested on their bones, though the terror of these warriors had stalked through the land of the living.
26Ezk 32:28 "You too, O Pharaoh, will be broken and will lie among the uncircumcised, with those killed by the sword.
26Ezk 32:29 "Edom is there, her kings and all her princes; despite their power, they are laid with those killed by the sword. They lie with the uncircumcised, with those who go down to the pit.
26Ezk 32:30 "All the princes of the north and all the Sidonians are there; they went down with the slain in disgrace despite the terror caused by their power. They lie uncircumcised with those killed by the sword and bear their shame with those who go down to the pit.
26Ezk 32:31 "Pharaoh--he and all his army--will see them and he will be consoled for all his hordes that were killed by the sword, declares the Sovereign LORD.
26Ezk 32:32 Although I had him spread terror in the land of the living, Pharaoh and all his hordes will be laid among the uncircumcised, with those killed by the sword, declares the Sovereign LORD."
26Ezk 33:1 The word of the LORD came to me£º
26Ezk 33:2 "Son of man, speak to your countrymen and say to them£º 'When I bring the sword against a land, and the people of the land choose one of their men and make him their watchman,
26Ezk 33:3 and he sees the sword coming against the land and blows the trumpet to warn the people,
26Ezk 33:4 then if anyone hears the trumpet but does not take warning and the sword comes and takes his life, his blood will be on his own head.
26Ezk 33:5 Since he heard the sound of the trumpet but did not take warning, his blood will be on his own head. If he had taken warning, he would have saved himself.
26Ezk 33:6 But if the watchman sees the sword coming and does not blow the trumpet to warn the people and the sword comes and takes the life of one of them, that man will be taken away because of his sin, but I will hold the watchman accountable for his blood.'
26Ezk 33:7 "Son of man, I have made you a watchman for the house of Israel; so hear the word I speak and give them warning from me.
26Ezk 33:8 When I say to the wicked, 'O wicked man, you will surely die,' and you do not speak out to dissuade him from his ways, that wicked man will die for his sin, and I will hold you accountable for his blood.
26Ezk 33:9 But if you do warn the wicked man to turn from his ways and he does not do so, he will die for his sin, but you will have saved yourself.
26Ezk 33:10 "Son of man, say to the house of Israel, 'This is what you are saying£º "Our offenses and sins weigh us down, and we are wasting away because of them. How then can we live?" '
26Ezk 33:11 Say to them, 'As surely as I live, declares the Sovereign LORD, I take no pleasure in the death of the wicked, but rather that they turn from their ways and live. Turn! Turn from your evil ways! Why will you die, O house of Israel?'
26Ezk 33:12 "Therefore, son of man, say to your countrymen, 'The righteousness of the righteous man will not save him when he disobeys, and the wickedness of the wicked man will not cause him to fall when he turns from it. The righteous man, if he sins, will not be allowed to live because of his former righteousness.'
26Ezk 33:13 If I tell the righteous man that he will surely live, but then he trusts in his righteousness and does evil, none of the righteous things he has done will be remembered; he will die for the evil he has done.
26Ezk 33:14 And if I say to the wicked man, 'You will surely die,' but he then turns away from his sin and does what is just and right--
26Ezk 33:15 if he gives back what he took in pledge for a loan, returns what he has stolen, follows the decrees that give life, and does no evil, he will surely live; he will not die.
26Ezk 33:16 None of the sins he has committed will be remembered against him. He has done what is just and right; he will surely live.
26Ezk 33:17 "Yet your countrymen say, 'The way of the Lord is not just.' But it is their way that is not just.
26Ezk 33:18 If a righteous man turns from his righteousness and does evil, he will die for it.
26Ezk 33:19 And if a wicked man turns away from his wickedness and does what is just and right, he will live by doing so.
26Ezk 33:20 Yet, O house of Israel, you say, 'The way of the Lord is not just.' But I will judge each of you according to his own ways."
26Ezk 33:21 In the twelfth year of our exile, in the tenth month on the fifth day, a man who had escaped from Jerusalem came to me and said, "The city has fallen!"
26Ezk 33:22 Now the evening before the man arrived, the hand of the LORD was upon me, and he opened my mouth before the man came to me in the morning. So my mouth was opened and I was no longer silent.
26Ezk 33:23 Then the word of the LORD came to me£º
26Ezk 33:24 "Son of man, the people living in those ruins in the land of Israel are saying, 'Abraham was only one man, yet he possessed the land. But we are many; surely the land has been given to us as our possession.'
26Ezk 33:25 Therefore say to them, 'This is what the Sovereign LORD says£º Since you eat meat with the blood still in it and look to your idols and shed blood, should you then possess the land?
26Ezk 33:26 You rely on your sword, you do detestable things, and each of you defiles his neighbor's wife. Should you then possess the land?'
26Ezk 33:27 "Say this to them£º 'This is what the Sovereign LORD says£º As surely as I live, those who are left in the ruins will fall by the sword, those out in the country I will give to the wild animals to be devoured, and those in strongholds and caves will die of a plague.
26Ezk 33:28 I will make the land a desolate waste, and her proud strength will come to an end, and the mountains of Israel will become desolate so that no one will cross them.
26Ezk 33:29 Then they will know that I am the LORD, when I have made the land a desolate waste because of all the detestable things they have done.'
26Ezk 33:30 "As for you, son of man, your countrymen are talking together about you by the walls and at the doors of the houses, saying to each other, 'Come and hear the message that has come from the LORD.'
26Ezk 33:31 My people come to you, as they usually do, and sit before you to listen to your words, but they do not put them into practice. With their mouths they express devotion, but their hearts are greedy for unjust gain.
26Ezk 33:32 Indeed, to them you are nothing more than one who sings love songs with a beautiful voice and plays an instrument well, for they hear your words but do not put them into practice.
26Ezk 33:33 "When all this comes true--and it surely will--then they will know that a prophet has been among them."
26Ezk 34:1 The word of the LORD came to me£º
26Ezk 34:2 "Son of man, prophesy against the shepherds of Israel; prophesy and say to them£º 'This is what the Sovereign LORD says£º Woe to the shepherds of Israel who only take care of themselves! Should not shepherds take care of the flock?
26Ezk 34:3 You eat the curds, clothe yourselves with the wool and slaughter the choice animals, but you do not take care of the flock.
26Ezk 34:4 You have not strengthened the weak or healed the sick or bound up the injured. You have not brought back the strays or searched for the lost. You have ruled them harshly and brutally.
26Ezk 34:5 So they were scattered because there was no shepherd, and when they were scattered they became food for all the wild animals.
26Ezk 34:6 My sheep wandered over all the mountains and on every high hill. They were scattered over the whole earth, and no one searched or looked for them.
26Ezk 34:7 "'Therefore, you shepherds, hear the word of the LORD£º
26Ezk 34:8 As surely as I live, declares the Sovereign LORD, because my flock lacks a shepherd and so has been plundered and has become food for all the wild animals, and because my shepherds did not search for my flock but cared for themselves rather than for my flock,
26Ezk 34:9 therefore, O shepherds, hear the word of the LORD£º
26Ezk 34:10 This is what the Sovereign LORD says£º I am against the shepherds and will hold them accountable for my flock. I will remove them from tending the flock so that the shepherds can no longer feed themselves. I will rescue my flock from their mouths, and it will no longer be food for them.
26Ezk 34:11 "'For this is what the Sovereign LORD says£º I myself will search for my sheep and look after them.
26Ezk 34:12 As a shepherd looks after his scattered flock when he is with them, so will I look after my sheep. I will rescue them from all the places where they were scattered on a day of clouds and darkness.
26Ezk 34:13 I will bring them out from the nations and gather them from the countries, and I will bring them into their own land. I will pasture them on the mountains of Israel, in the ravines and in all the settlements in the land.
26Ezk 34:14 I will tend them in a good pasture, and the mountain heights of Israel will be their grazing land. There they will lie down in good grazing land, and there they will feed in a rich pasture on the mountains of Israel.
26Ezk 34:15 I myself will tend my sheep and have them lie down, declares the Sovereign LORD.
26Ezk 34:16 I will search for the lost and bring back the strays. I will bind up the injured and strengthen the weak, but the sleek and the strong I will destroy. I will shepherd the flock with justice.
26Ezk 34:17 "'As for you, my flock, this is what the Sovereign LORD says£º I will judge between one sheep and another, and between rams and goats.
26Ezk 34:18 Is it not enough for you to feed on the good pasture? Must you also trample the rest of your pasture with your feet? Is it not enough for you to drink clear water? Must you also muddy the rest with your feet?
26Ezk 34:19 Must my flock feed on what you have trampled and drink what you have muddied with your feet?
26Ezk 34:20 "'Therefore this is what the Sovereign LORD says to them£º See, I myself will judge between the fat sheep and the lean sheep.
26Ezk 34:21 Because you shove with flank and shoulder, butting all the weak sheep with your horns until you have driven them away,
26Ezk 34:22 I will save my flock, and they will no longer be plundered. I will judge between one sheep and another.
26Ezk 34:23 I will place over them one shepherd, my servant David, and he will tend them; he will tend them and be their shepherd.
26Ezk 34:24 I the LORD will be their God, and my servant David will be prince among them. I the LORD have spoken.
26Ezk 34:25 "'I will make a covenant of peace with them and rid the land of wild beasts so that they may live in the desert and sleep in the forests in safety.
26Ezk 34:26 I will bless them and the places surrounding my hill. I will send down showers in season; there will be showers of blessing.
26Ezk 34:27 The trees of the field will yield their fruit and the ground will yield its crops; the people will be secure in their land. They will know that I am the LORD, when I break the bars of their yoke and rescue them from the hands of those who enslaved them.
26Ezk 34:28 They will no longer be plundered by the nations, nor will wild animals devour them. They will live in safety, and no one will make them afraid.
26Ezk 34:29 I will provide for them a land renowned for its crops, and they will no longer be victims of famine in the land or bear the scorn of the nations.
26Ezk 34:30 Then they will know that I, the LORD their God, am with them and that they, the house of Israel, are my people, declares the Sovereign LORD.
26Ezk 34:31 You my sheep, the sheep of my pasture, are people, and I am your God, declares the Sovereign LORD.'"
26Ezk 35:1 The word of the LORD came to me£º
26Ezk 35:2 "Son of man, set your face against Mount Seir; prophesy against it
26Ezk 35:3 and say£º 'This is what the Sovereign LORD says£º I am against you, Mount Seir, and I will stretch out my hand against you and make you a desolate waste.
26Ezk 35:4 I will turn your towns into ruins and you will be desolate. Then you will know that I am the LORD.
26Ezk 35:5 "'Because you harbored an ancient hostility and delivered the Israelites over to the sword at the time of their calamity, the time their punishment reached its climax,
26Ezk 35:6 therefore as surely as I live, declares the Sovereign LORD, I will give you over to bloodshed and it will pursue you. Since you did not hate bloodshed, bloodshed will pursue you.
26Ezk 35:7 I will make Mount Seir a desolate waste and cut off from it all who come and go.
26Ezk 35:8 I will fill your mountains with the slain; those killed by the sword will fall on your hills and in your valleys and in all your ravines.
26Ezk 35:9 I will make you desolate forever; your towns will not be inhabited. Then you will know that I am the LORD.
26Ezk 35:10 "'Because you have said, "These two nations and countries will be ours and we will take possession of them," even though I the LORD was there,
26Ezk 35:11 therefore as surely as I live, declares the Sovereign LORD, I will treat you in accordance with the anger and jealousy you showed in your hatred of them and I will make myself known among them when I judge you.
26Ezk 35:12 Then you will know that I the LORD have heard all the contemptible things you have said against the mountains of Israel. You said, "They have been laid waste and have been given over to us to devour."
26Ezk 35:13 You boasted against me and spoke against me without restraint, and I heard it.
26Ezk 35:14 This is what the Sovereign LORD says£º While the whole earth rejoices, I will make you desolate.
26Ezk 35:15 Because you rejoiced when the inheritance of the house of Israel became desolate, that is how I will treat you. You will be desolate, O Mount Seir, you and all of Edom. Then they will know that I am the LORD.'"
26Ezk 36:1 "Son of man, prophesy to the mountains of Israel and say, 'O mountains of Israel, hear the word of the LORD.
26Ezk 36:2 This is what the Sovereign LORD says£º The enemy said of you, "Aha! The ancient heights have become our possession." '
26Ezk 36:3 Therefore prophesy and say, 'This is what the Sovereign LORD says£º Because they ravaged and hounded you from every side so that you became the possession of the rest of the nations and the object of people's malicious talk and slander,
26Ezk 36:4 therefore, O mountains of Israel, hear the word of the Sovereign LORD£º This is what the Sovereign LORD says to the mountains and hills, to the ravines and valleys, to the desolate ruins and the deserted towns that have been plundered and ridiculed by the rest of the nations around you--
26Ezk 36:5 this is what the Sovereign LORD says£º In my burning zeal I have spoken against the rest of the nations, and against all Edom, for with glee and with malice in their hearts they made my land their own possession so that they might plunder its pastureland.'
26Ezk 36:6 Therefore prophesy concerning the land of Israel and say to the mountains and hills, to the ravines and valleys£º 'This is what the Sovereign LORD says£º I speak in my jealous wrath because you have suffered the scorn of the nations.
26Ezk 36:7 Therefore this is what the Sovereign LORD says£º I swear with uplifted hand that the nations around you will also suffer scorn.
26Ezk 36:8 "'But you, O mountains of Israel, will produce branches and fruit for my people Israel, for they will soon come home.
26Ezk 36:9 I am concerned for you and will look on you with favor; you will be plowed and sown,
26Ezk 36:10 and I will multiply the number of people upon you, even the whole house of Israel. The towns will be inhabited and the ruins rebuilt.
26Ezk 36:11 I will increase the number of men and animals upon you, and they will be fruitful and become numerous. I will settle people on you as in the past and will make you prosper more than before. Then you will know that I am the LORD.
26Ezk 36:12 I will cause people, my people Israel, to walk upon you. They will possess you, and you will be their inheritance; you will never again deprive them of their children.
26Ezk 36:13 "'This is what the Sovereign LORD says£º Because people say to you, "You devour men and deprive your nation of its children,"
26Ezk 36:14 therefore you will no longer devour men or make your nation childless, declares the Sovereign LORD.
26Ezk 36:15 No longer will I make you hear the taunts of the nations, and no longer will you suffer the scorn of the peoples or cause your nation to fall, declares the Sovereign LORD.'"
26Ezk 36:16 Again the word of the LORD came to me£º
26Ezk 36:17 "Son of man, when the people of Israel were living in their own land, they defiled it by their conduct and their actions. Their conduct was like a woman's monthly uncleanness in my sight.
26Ezk 36:18 So I poured out my wrath on them because they had shed blood in the land and because they had defiled it with their idols.
26Ezk 36:19 I dispersed them among the nations, and they were scattered through the countries; I judged them according to their conduct and their actions.
26Ezk 36:20 And wherever they went among the nations they profaned my holy name, for it was said of them, 'These are the LORD'S people, and yet they had to leave his land.'
26Ezk 36:21 I had concern for my holy name, which the house of Israel profaned among the nations where they had gone.
26Ezk 36:22 "Therefore say to the house of Israel, 'This is what the Sovereign LORD says£º It is not for your sake, O house of Israel, that I am going to do these things, but for the sake of my holy name, which you have profaned among the nations where you have gone.
26Ezk 36:23 I will show the holiness of my great name, which has been profaned among the nations, the name you have profaned among them. Then the nations will know that I am the LORD, declares the Sovereign LORD, when I show myself holy through you before their eyes.
26Ezk 36:24 "'For I will take you out of the nations; I will gather you from all the countries and bring you back into your own land.
26Ezk 36:25 I will sprinkle clean water on you, and you will be clean; I will cleanse you from all your impurities and from all your idols.
26Ezk 36:26 I will give you a new heart and put a new spirit in you; I will remove from you your heart of stone and give you a heart of flesh.
26Ezk 36:27 And I will put my Spirit in you and move you to follow my decrees and be careful to keep my laws.
26Ezk 36:28 You will live in the land I gave your forefathers; you will be my people, and I will be your God.
26Ezk 36:29 I will save you from all your uncleanness. I will call for the grain and make it plentiful and will not bring famine upon you.
26Ezk 36:30 I will increase the fruit of the trees and the crops of the field, so that you will no longer suffer disgrace among the nations because of famine.
26Ezk 36:31 Then you will remember your evil ways and wicked deeds, and you will loathe yourselves for your sins and detestable practices.
26Ezk 36:32 I want you to know that I am not doing this for your sake, declares the Sovereign LORD. Be ashamed and disgraced for your conduct, O house of Israel!
26Ezk 36:33 "'This is what the Sovereign LORD says£º On the day I cleanse you from all your sins, I will resettle your towns, and the ruins will be rebuilt.
26Ezk 36:34 The desolate land will be cultivated instead of lying desolate in the sight of all who pass through it.
26Ezk 36:35 They will say, "This land that was laid waste has become like the garden of Eden; the cities that were lying in ruins, desolate and destroyed, are now fortified and inhabited."
26Ezk 36:36 Then the nations around you that remain will know that I the LORD have rebuilt what was destroyed and have replanted what was desolate. I the LORD have spoken, and I will do it.'
26Ezk 36:37 "This is what the Sovereign LORD says£º Once again I will yield to the plea of the house of Israel and do this for them£º I will make their people as numerous as sheep,
26Ezk 36:38 as numerous as the flocks for offerings at Jerusalem during her appointed feasts. So will the ruined cities be filled with flocks of people. Then they will know that I am the LORD."
26Ezk 37:1 The hand of the LORD was upon me, and he brought me out by the Spirit of the LORD and set me in the middle of a valley; it was full of bones.
26Ezk 37:2 He led me back and forth among them, and I saw a great many bones on the floor of the valley, bones that were very dry.
26Ezk 37:3 He asked me, "Son of man, can these bones live?" I said, "O Sovereign LORD, you alone know."
26Ezk 37:4 Then he said to me, "Prophesy to these bones and say to them, 'Dry bones, hear the word of the LORD!
26Ezk 37:5 This is what the Sovereign LORD says to these bones£º I will make breath enter you, and you will come to life.
26Ezk 37:6 I will attach tendons to you and make flesh come upon you and cover you with skin; I will put breath in you, and you will come to life. Then you will know that I am the LORD.'"
26Ezk 37:7 So I prophesied as I was commanded. And as I was prophesying, there was a noise, a rattling sound, and the bones came together, bone to bone.
26Ezk 37:8 I looked, and tendons and flesh appeared on them and skin covered them, but there was no breath in them.
26Ezk 37:9 Then he said to me, "Prophesy to the breath; prophesy, son of man, and say to it, 'This is what the Sovereign LORD says£º Come from the four winds, O breath, and breathe into these slain, that they may live.'"
26Ezk 37:10 So I prophesied as he commanded me, and breath entered them; they came to life and stood up on their feet--a vast army.
26Ezk 37:11 Then he said to me£º "Son of man, these bones are the whole house of Israel. They say, 'Our bones are dried up and our hope is gone; we are cut off.'
26Ezk 37:12 Therefore prophesy and say to them£º 'This is what the Sovereign LORD says£º O my people, I am going to open your graves and bring you up from them; I will bring you back to the land of Israel.
26Ezk 37:13 Then you, my people, will know that I am the LORD, when I open your graves and bring you up from them.
26Ezk 37:14 I will put my Spirit in you and you will live, and I will settle you in your own land. Then you will know that I the LORD have spoken, and I have done it, declares the LORD.'"
26Ezk 37:15 The word of the LORD came to me£º
26Ezk 37:16 "Son of man, take a stick of wood and write on it, 'Belonging to Judah and the Israelites associated with him.' Then take another stick of wood, and write on it, 'Ephraim's stick, belonging to Joseph and all the house of Israel associated with him.'
26Ezk 37:17 Join them together into one stick so that they will become one in your hand.
26Ezk 37:18 "When your countrymen ask you, 'Won't you tell us what you mean by this?'
26Ezk 37:19 say to them, 'This is what the Sovereign LORD says£º I am going to take the stick of Joseph--which is in Ephraim's hand--and of the Israelite tribes associated with him, and join it to Judah's stick, making them a single stick of wood, and they will become one in my hand.'
26Ezk 37:20 Hold before their eyes the sticks you have written on
26Ezk 37:21 and say to them, 'This is what the Sovereign LORD says£º I will take the Israelites out of the nations where they have gone. I will gather them from all around and bring them back into their own land.
26Ezk 37:22 I will make them one nation in the land, on the mountains of Israel. There will be one king over all of them and they will never again be two nations or be divided into two kingdoms.
26Ezk 37:23 They will no longer defile themselves with their idols and vile images or with any of their offenses, for I will save them from all their sinful backsliding, and I will cleanse them. They will be my people, and I will be their God.
26Ezk 37:24 "'My servant David will be king over them, and they will all have one shepherd. They will follow my laws and be careful to keep my decrees.
26Ezk 37:25 They will live in the land I gave to my servant Jacob, the land where your fathers lived. They and their children and their children's children will live there forever, and David my servant will be their prince forever.
26Ezk 37:26 I will make a covenant of peace with them; it will be an everlasting covenant. I will establish them and increase their numbers, and I will put my sanctuary among them forever.
26Ezk 37:27 My dwelling place will be with them; I will be their God, and they will be my people.
26Ezk 37:28 Then the nations will know that I the LORD make Israel holy, when my sanctuary is among them forever.'"
26Ezk 38:1 The word of the LORD came to me£º
26Ezk 38:2 "Son of man, set your face against Gog, of the land of Magog, the chief prince of Meshech and Tubal; prophesy against him
26Ezk 38:3 and say£º 'This is what the Sovereign LORD says£º I am against you, O Gog, chief prince of Meshech and Tubal.
26Ezk 38:4 I will turn you around, put hooks in your jaws and bring you out with your whole army--your horses, your horsemen fully armed, and a great horde with large and small shields, all of them brandishing their swords.
26Ezk 38:5 Persia, Cush and Put will be with them, all with shields and helmets,
26Ezk 38:6 also Gomer with all its troops, and Beth Togarmah from the far north with all its troops--the many nations with you.
26Ezk 38:7 "'Get ready; be prepared, you and all the hordes gathered about you, and take command of them.
26Ezk 38:8 After many days you will be called to arms. In future years you will invade a land that has recovered from war, whose people were gathered from many nations to the mountains of Israel, which had long been desolate. They had been brought out from the nations, and now all of them live in safety.
26Ezk 38:9 You and all your troops and the many nations with you will go up, advancing like a storm; you will be like a cloud covering the land.
26Ezk 38:10 "'This is what the Sovereign LORD says£º On that day thoughts will come into your mind and you will devise an evil scheme.
26Ezk 38:11 You will say, "I will invade a land of unwalled villages; I will attack a peaceful and unsuspecting people--all of them living without walls and without gates and bars.
26Ezk 38:12 I will plunder and loot and turn my hand against the resettled ruins and the people gathered from the nations, rich in livestock and goods, living at the center of the land."
26Ezk 38:13 Sheba and Dedan and the merchants of Tarshish and all her villages will say to you, "Have you come to plunder? Have you gathered your hordes to loot, to carry off silver and gold, to take away livestock and goods and to seize much plunder?" '
26Ezk 38:14 "Therefore, son of man, prophesy and say to Gog£º 'This is what the Sovereign LORD says£º In that day, when my people Israel are living in safety, will you not take notice of it?
26Ezk 38:15 You will come from your place in the far north, you and many nations with you, all of them riding on horses, a great horde, a mighty army.
26Ezk 38:16 You will advance against my people Israel like a cloud that covers the land. In days to come, O Gog, I will bring you against my land, so that the nations may know me when I show myself holy through you before their eyes.
26Ezk 38:17 "'This is what the Sovereign LORD says£º Are you not the one I spoke of in former days by my servants the prophets of Israel? At that time they prophesied for years that I would bring you against them.
26Ezk 38:18 This is what will happen in that day£º When Gog attacks the land of Israel, my hot anger will be aroused, declares the Sovereign LORD.
26Ezk 38:19 In my zeal and fiery wrath I declare that at that time there shall be a great earthquake in the land of Israel.
26Ezk 38:20 The fish of the sea, the birds of the air, the beasts of the field, every creature that moves along the ground, and all the people on the face of the earth will tremble at my presence. The mountains will be overturned, the cliffs will crumble and every wall will fall to the ground.
26Ezk 38:21 I will summon a sword against Gog on all my mountains, declares the Sovereign LORD. Every man's sword will be against his brother.
26Ezk 38:22 I will execute judgment upon him with plague and bloodshed; I will pour down torrents of rain, hailstones and burning sulfur on him and on his troops and on the many nations with him.
26Ezk 38:23 And so I will show my greatness and my holiness, and I will make myself known in the sight of many nations. Then they will know that I am the LORD.'
26Ezk 39:1 "Son of man, prophesy against Gog and say£º 'This is what the Sovereign LORD says£º I am against you, O Gog, chief prince of Meshech and Tubal.
26Ezk 39:2 I will turn you around and drag you along. I will bring you from the far north and send you against the mountains of Israel.
26Ezk 39:3 Then I will strike your bow from your left hand and make your arrows drop from your right hand.
26Ezk 39:4 On the mountains of Israel you will fall, you and all your troops and the nations with you. I will give you as food to all kinds of carrion birds and to the wild animals.
26Ezk 39:5 You will fall in the open field, for I have spoken, declares the Sovereign LORD.
26Ezk 39:6 I will send fire on Magog and on those who live in safety in the coastlands, and they will know that I am the LORD.
26Ezk 39:7 "'I will make known my holy name among my people Israel. I will no longer let my holy name be profaned, and the nations will know that I the LORD am the Holy One in Israel.
26Ezk 39:8 It is coming! It will surely take place, declares the Sovereign LORD. This is the day I have spoken of.
26Ezk 39:9 "'Then those who live in the towns of Israel will go out and use the weapons for fuel and burn them up--the small and large shields, the bows and arrows, the war clubs and spears. For seven years they will use them for fuel.
26Ezk 39:10 They will not need to gather wood from the fields or cut it from the forests, because they will use the weapons for fuel. And they will plunder those who plundered them and loot those who looted them, declares the Sovereign LORD.
26Ezk 39:11 "'On that day I will give Gog a burial place in Israel, in the valley of those who travel east toward the Sea. It will block the way of travelers, because Gog and all his hordes will be buried there. So it will be called the Valley of Hamon Gog.
26Ezk 39:12 "'For seven months the house of Israel will be burying them in order to cleanse the land.
26Ezk 39:13 All the people of the land will bury them, and the day I am glorified will be a memorable day for them, declares the Sovereign LORD.
26Ezk 39:14 "'Men will be regularly employed to cleanse the land. Some will go throughout the land and, in addition to them, others will bury those that remain on the ground. At the end of the seven months they will begin their search.
26Ezk 39:15 As they go through the land and one of them sees a human bone, he will set up a marker beside it until the gravediggers have buried it in the Valley of Hamon Gog.
